(554, 'Startup Terrace at VIVA TECHNOLOGY 2023: call for startups to participate!', '2023-04-06', '', '<div dir=\"auto\">In 2023, the first stop for the startup landing in Europe is Paris! The 2023 VIVA TECHNOLOGY is available for applications from now!&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">France has put lots of effort and resources into developing innovative technology and support for startups. Now, France has become the benchmark when it comes to the startup ecosystem. Also, VIVA TECH is now one of the main startup expos, with lots of companies and attendees visiting Paris every year.</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">This year (2023), the Small and Medium Enterprise Administration (SMEA), Division of the Ministry of Economic Affairs will keep leading Taiwanese startups to enter the European market with every effort and support. Hope through strengthening international connections, we can show the innovation from Taiwan to the globe.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">This time, we plan to land in Paris. The selected 5 outstanding startup teams will have the training boot camp, visit the startup ecosystem stakeholders, and participate in VIVA TECH. Through the journey, startups can have more exposure and explore the potential.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">Qualifications:</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">Startups fitted the definition of Startup according to SMEA, registered in Taiwan. Startups set up within 8 years, mainly developing solutions regarding Climate Tech, IoT, AI, Deep Tech, and Web 3.0.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">Startups working on developing new products or technologies, integrating new business models, or considering Europe their main target market.</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">Besides, startups signed up in VIVA TECH innovation challenges: <a href=\"https://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Fchallenges.vivatechnology.com%2Fen%2Fchallenges%3Ffbclid%3DIwAR3uQMRWnN1v1vKQZaJcmtOYir5H5NyBabB6ytnjWIYmKo2qa7OwXKFYUyI&amp;h=AT2oC8j20--LW3wbej9kOiM6rtGjmvoSi2e34c8cmOFFnq2hdsCQsBNHXf4IAzDwUUJVHzo0uzr-LSXOCOzMNuLKTI0ysL5PD3rfN0CEBumjTLvZeGbFVpyAgb_zSPoSsBn4&amp;__tn__=-UK-y-R&amp;c[0]=AT1Hgo5SrU0--3Bg_J6Y_-xyW6-XDrhe0z-UUYoCXXbHISZ2Zdd2B02mrmWyIT0iCPWfE3vWTDEJqEsohHuWsjVb8J9xQ6Rmw5wQue_fXGzYCfn9-ihqhWndW4kUZkgtx5yjGvLvMj0VpAQYhzouTKidPxzsNLiVCGWiMeOUtJ8lQ8jXM896hr7MYOEBfPPGBCH3mj8VBAOZDAtKDsN1oJpZfY7BrBNkIQ33\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" tabindex=\"0\" target=\"_blank\">https://challenges.vivatechnology.com/en/challenges</a> or viewed as gazelle companies (according to OECD) would be preferred.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">See you in Paris</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">\r\n	<br>\r\n</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\"><strong>Event Information</strong></div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">-Registration link: <a href=\"https://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Fseminars.tca.org.tw%2FD10o03862.aspx%3Ffbclid%3DIwAR3XBNSoChU6HxS3TE1JS4Tkjpyze5jx05j8t9DMA0KyQZit5kP58K4A2_Q&amp;h=AT25c43ebwl9OtEtHpcRfQrMgVZH1WW6YGR3i1zt-hU0l0RBycQBek8kvK14sKTHysFgZyrB4yV_gAHpZxyxg6zE2MtcFt0lGvOE_lMbTtbJAU2lfNsLGU7hADFhXt3kYCZ-&amp;__tn__=-UK-y-R&amp;c[0]=AT1Hgo5SrU0--3Bg_J6Y_-xyW6-XDrhe0z-UUYoCXXbHISZ2Zdd2B02mrmWyIT0iCPWfE3vWTDEJqEsohHuWsjVb8J9xQ6Rmw5wQue_fXGzYCfn9-ihqhWndW4kUZkgtx5yjGvLvMj0VpAQYhzouTKidPxzsNLiVCGWiMeOUtJ8lQ8jXM896hr7MYOEBfPPGBCH3mj8VBAOZDAtKDsN1oJpZfY7BrBNkIQ33\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" tabindex=\"0\" target=\"_blank\">https://seminars.tca.org.tw/D10o03862.aspx</a></div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">-Contact: Ms. Wendy</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">-Contact number / Email: 02-2577-4249 #522 / <a href=\"mailto:wendylee@mail.tca.org.tw\">wendylee@mail.tca.org.tw</a>\r\n	<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\"><strong>Schedule</strong></div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">-Registration period: from now until April 10th, 2023</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">-Result of First Round Selection: April 19th,2023</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">-Second Round Pitch: April 26th,2023</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">-Final Result Announcement: May 3rd, 2023</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">The final selection announcement will be notified to the selected team by email on May 3rd, 2023. Please noted that if the startup teams are not selected, no further notice will be sent. Please pay attention to incoming emails, thank you.</div>', NULL, 1, '2023-04-10 09:22:55', '2023-04-10 09:22:55', NULL),
(555, 'National Development Council aims to loosen the financial regulations for Gold Card holders and foreign professionals in Taiwan', '2023-04-10', '', '<blockquote>\r\n\r\n	<p>The National Development Council has received feedback regarding the difficulties that foreign professionals face when applying for banking accounts and credit cards in Taiwan. To address this issue, the council plans to coordinate with four government-owned banks to provide specialized services, as a first step towards improvement.</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p>On March 20th, the minister of the National Development Council(NDC), Ming-Hsin Kung, gathers several key startup communities in Taiwan, including AAMA, AppWorks, Meet Global, Darwin Ventures, Garage+, Sparklabs Taiwan and Startup Island TAIWAN to discuss ways to improve Taiwan\'s startup ecosystem. The attending representatives provided many valuable opinions on funding injections, expanding overseas, talent introduction, and regulatory relaxation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Minister Ming-Hsin Kung announces several measures to strengthen Taiwan\'s startup environment for attracting foreign professionals and to strengthen Taiwan’s presence in oversea countries. To address the difficulty of foreign professionals applying for banking accounts in Taiwan, he will strengthen the coordination with four banks to provide specialized services. To expand overseas business opportunities for startups, he also announced that NDC will visit Tokyo and countries in the New Southbound Policy again this year to enhance bilateral exchanges</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"/en/storage/app/media/uploaded-files/1681118838537.jpeg\" alt=\"shutterstock_141326002_bank online_old\" class=\"fr-fic fr-dii\" data-result=\"success\" style=\"width: 900px;\"></p>\r\n\r\n<p>To address the difficulty of foreign professionals applying for banking accounts in Taiwan, Minister Ming-Hsin Kung will strengthen the coordination with four banks to provide specialized services. / Photograph : Robert Kneschke via shutterstock</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For the \"COVID-19 Impact Startup Equity Investment Special Project\" launched by the National Development Fund(NDF) in 2020, Minister Ming-Hsin Kung hopes NDF to refer other departments’ relief loan mechanisms, and let startups extend the payment deadline.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Trying to solve the banking problems for foreign professionals</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The attending representatives from startup communities also emphasize the importance of attracting global talents. NDC responds that they are aware and will try to implement more measures to make Taiwan friendlier to foreign professionals.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"/en/storage/app/media/uploaded-files/1681118875968.jpeg\" alt=\"taiwan-gold-card-media-image-en\" class=\"fr-fic fr-dii\" data-result=\"success\" style=\"width: 900px;\"></p>\r\n\r\n<p>NDC is working with government-owned banks, Taiwan Bank, First Bank, Mega Bank, and Hua Nan Bank, to help Employment Gold Card holders in applying for credit cards. / Photograph : Gold Card Official Website</p>\r\n\r\n<p>NDC is working with government-owned banks, Taiwan Bank, First Bank, Mega Bank, and Hua Nan Bank, to help Employment Gold Card holders in applying for credit cards. Not only has a bilingual service section been set up on the website for Employment Gold Card holders, but also 24-hour customer service hotline has been provided. In addition, the Financial Supervisory Commission has also sent a letter to the Bankers Association urging banks to actively improve their bilingual services.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As of the end of December 2022, 23 banks have set up 827 bilingual branches, providing first-line bilingual service counters and bilingual financial services, which is a 3.8-fold increase from the 172 branches set up by 18 banks at the end of December 2020.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Minister Ming-Hsin Kung also plans to extend the service provided by the Employment Gold Card to foreign professionals.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>〔Original :Meet Global〕\r\n	<br><a href=\"https://meet-global.bnext.com.tw/articles/view/47892\">https://meet-global.bnext.com.tw/articles/view/47892</a></p>', NULL, 1, '2023-04-10 09:31:16', '2023-09-25 13:43:10', NULL),
(556, 'Crowdfunding is a great strategy to go into the Japanese market: Interview with GREEN FUNDING and TAIWAN TSUTAYA', '2023-04-11', '', '<blockquote>\r\n\r\n	<p>Yusuke Takahashi, Global Partners Chief Director of Japanese crowdfunding platform GREEN FUNDING, and Ryunosuke Hashimoto, General Manager of TAIWAN TSUTAYA, recently visited Taiwan to strengthen collaboration in the crowdfunding market between Taiwan and Japan.</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p>GREEN FUNDING is a crowdfunding platform under the Japanese CCC (TSUTAYA) group. The CCC group has over 70 million members in Japan and operates various physica retaill stores such as \"TSUTAYA,\" \"TSUTAYA BOOKSTORES,\" \"TSUTAYA ELECTRONICS,\" and \"SHARE LOUNGE.\"</p>\r\n\r\n<p>“One of the missions for us to come to Taiwan is to help more brands enter the Japanese market,” said Yusuke Takahashi, Global Partners Chief Director of GREEN FUNDING.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"/en/storage/app/media/uploaded-files/1681119254014.jpeg\" alt=\"Green Funding\" class=\"fr-fic fr-dii\" data-result=\"success\" style=\"width: 900px;\"></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Yusuke Takahashi, Global Partners Chief Director of Japanese crowdfunding platform GREEN FUNDING, and Ryunosuke Hashimoto, General Manager of TAIWAN TSUTAYA, recently visited Taiwan to strengthen collaboration in the crowdfunding market between Taiwan and Japan. / Photograph : Chi Ko</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Japan is the world’s third largest economic power and the Japanese market is always Taiwanese and many countries\' primary overseas market. But due to the cultural differences, talents, and Japan’s unique trading company business model, it is not an easy job to enter the Japanese market. “I think crowdfunding is a great way to test whether your product can fit the Japanese market, ” said Takahashi.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>“After accumulating enough domestic consumers, many Taiwanese teams will consider entering the overseas market through crowdfunding. Compared to other countries, Taiwanese teams have the similar design style with Japan, which means relatively low difficulty in entering the Japanese market,” said Takahashi.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>TAIWAN TSUTAYA General Manager Ryunosuke Hashimoto emphasize that TSUTAYA BOOKSTORE already partnered with several Taiwanese brands and is experienced on bring Taiwanese brands to the Japanese market. TSUTAYA can act as an agent for Taiwanese company during the crowdfunding campaign and Taiwanese company do need to establish a Japanese subsidiary.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Takahashi also mentioned that it is also imporatant to obtain certified security certificates, professional institution certifications, or ensure that the product complies with regulatory standards before launching a crowdfunding campaign.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Strengthen the tie with Taiwanese market</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Last month, GREEN FUNDING conduct a series of campaign to strengthen the tie with Taiwanese market. They host the 3rd event of iiiNNO TAIWAN TSUTAYA PROGRAM (iTTP) and invited 6 companies to the pitch event. The Taiwan strategy manager Sandy Lin attended Business Next Media’s monthly startup event to be the keynote speaker to share how GREEN FUNDING can help Taiwan’s product softlanding in the Japan.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"/en/storage/app/media/uploaded-files/1681119285062.jpeg\" alt=\"GREEN FUNDING\" class=\"fr-fic fr-dii\" data-result=\"success\" style=\"width: 900px;\"></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sandy Lin attended Business Next Media’s monthly startup event to be the keynote speaker to share how GREEN FUNDING can help Taiwan’s product softlanding in the Japan. / Photograph : Vincent Tseng</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Now GREEN FUNDING has specialists stationed in Taiwan to help make the communication smoother. With stronger and stronger Taiwan and Japan economic interaction, it is expected that GREEN FUNDING can be an important bridge for the crowdfunding market.</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n\r\n	<p>2023 E-Mobility Forum &gt; Lead the Way to 2035\r\n		<br>Getting a head start in the global electric vehicle industry: Integrating soft and hard advantages to seize opportunities.\r\n		<br>＃Trends &amp; Foresight＃Green Transformation＃Industry Layout＃Empowerment Through Semiconductors\r\n		<br>Register &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; <a href=\"https://edm.bnext.com.tw/leadtheway2035_en/\" target=\"_blank\">https://edm.bnext.com.tw/leadtheway2035_en/</a></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p>〔Original :Meet Global〕\r\n	<br><a href=\"https://meet-global.bnext.com.tw/articles/view/47896\">https://meet-global.bnext.com.tw/articles/view/47896</a></p>', NULL, 1, '2023-04-10 09:37:46', '2023-09-25 13:40:35', NULL),
(557, '2023 Go Global Startup Bootcamp', '2023-04-12', '', '<p>Are you struggling with how to market your company overseas? Not sure which market is suitable for your company? Unsure of how to find the right investment channels?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To assist startups, Taiwan Startup Stadium &amp; Startup Island TAIWAN will hold a series of two Level Up Bootcamp training events in April and May. These events will not only teach you how to package your brand to expand overseas from Taiwan but also guide you on how to raise funds more smoothly, making your company\'s growth journey less lonely!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The two events, Go Global Bootcamp and Term Sheet Bootcamp, provide training courses featuring training programs to promote insight for Taiwanese startups entering the global market.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We will invite experienced practitioners in the fields of PR, Marketing Strategy, and Investments to provide training and share their expertise.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Now, Kick off your global journey by signing up for the first event now: Go Global Startup Bootcamp!</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>***&nbsp;</strong>Please apply using this <strong><a href=\"https://www.surveycake.com/s/nZeVK\">Form</a>&nbsp;</strong>\r\n	<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In the past few years, with the impact of the pandemic, has your company prepared to expand into overseas markets? Or do you have ideas but are lacking that final push?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Expanding into overseas markets can be a challenging choice for startups. It\'s not only important to understand local employment culture and market trends, but also to know how to develop a suitable marketing strategy and promote your products.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Following last year\'s successful event, TSS and SIT are once again collaborating to host the Go Global Startup Bootcamp this year. The event aims to provide start-ups with strategies and tips on how to expand into overseas markets, and to help them avoid any potential pitfalls.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The training and sharing in this event will cover five key topic:\r\n	<br>1. Internal operations\r\n	<br>2. Build your Startup online profiles and BD tips\r\n	<br>3. Public Relations Strategy\r\n	<br>4. Marketing Strategy\r\n	<br>5. Fireside chat: Experience of expanding to overseas markets\r\n	<br>\r\n	<br>Startup members who participate in the event will receive individual brand image counseling and advice from industry experts or trainers. They can also enjoy a discounted price when signing up for the Term Sheet Bootcamp series of events, where they can learn about the ins and outs of fundraising.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Join us at the Go Global Startup Bootcamp and get ready to take your startup to the next level!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This event is mainly suitable for startups established within two years and those who are willing to expand their markets overseas.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, if your startup is already expanding overseas, you are also welcome to share your experience with the attendees or let your team members participate in the training.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Agenda:</strong>\r\n	<br>9:30-10:00. Sign-in &amp; Networking\r\n	<br>10:00-10:10 Opening\r\n	<br>10:10-10:30 Around the Room\r\n	<br>10:30-11:15 Internal operations\r\n	<br>11:15-12:00 Build your Startup online profiles and BD tips\r\n	<br>12:00-13:30 Networking Lunch\r\n	<br>13:30-14:30&nbsp;Public Relations Strategy\r\n	<br>14:30-15:30&nbsp;Marketing Strategy\r\n	<br>15:30-15:45&nbsp;Tea Break\r\n	<br>15:45-16:45&nbsp;Fireside chat: Experience of expanding overseas markets\r\n	<br>16:45-17:15&nbsp;Closing + Group photo + Networking</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Speakers:</strong>\r\n	<br>Lorenz Chen - Interim General Manager, Glints\r\n	<br>Chloe Ku -&nbsp;Head of Taiwan, PR Newswire, Cision APAC\r\n	<br>Allen John Ku&nbsp;-&nbsp;Director, Startup Island TAIWAN\r\n	<br>Stephanie Yu&nbsp;-&nbsp;Strategic Partnership, Kdan Mobile\r\n	<br>Victor Tseng -&nbsp;Chief Financial Officer, KKday\r\n	<br>Charlene Kuo -&nbsp;Global Strategy Lead, Strategy Office, FunNow\r\n	<br>Frinny Lee -&nbsp;CEO &amp; Founder, A.V. Mapping</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Note:</strong>\r\n	<br>* Event is FREE with limited spots\r\n	<br>* Registration ends on 4/20, make sure you sig-up before that!\r\n	<br>* This bootcamp will be conducted in English.\r\n	<br>* Discounts will be available for signing up for the next event \"Term Sheet Bootcamp\" with attendance.\r\n	<br>* TSS &amp; SIT reserves the right to change the terms and conditions to this event at any time without prior notice. In the case that any changes are made, the revised terms and conditions shall be posted on the event page immediately. Please check the latest information to inform yourself of any changes.\r\n	<br>* You\'ll receive a confirmation/rejection email by April 21, so pay careful attention to your mailbox.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>More Info:<a href=\"https://pse.is/4vn5lw\">https://pse.is/4vn5lw</a></p>', NULL, 1, '2023-04-11 01:26:19', '2023-04-11 01:58:57', NULL),
(558, 'PackAge+ raised 1.7M pre-series A, leveraging AI and helping to make the semiconductor supply chain greener', '2023-04-18', '', '<blockquote>\r\n\r\n	<p>Circular economy startup PackAge+ announced that it has raised $USD 1.7 million in pre-series A funding. According to the founder and CEO of PackAge+ Ye De Wei, the goal of this funding round is to accelerate the company\'s circular packaging scale, expand diversified services to create diversified revenue, and expand internationally.</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p>A large number of return stations have become the cornerstone of PackAge+\'s future plans. Ye De Wei said that this fundraising is to allow PackAge+ to develop diversified business models and focus on the development of more circular service application scenarios, such as sharing return stations with circular cups, circular lunch boxes, and other circular startups, to expand the energy of shared circular services.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ye De Wei also revealed that PackAge+ is collecting various data points from the circular system to build an AI model that calculates the best recycling route, which means the least carbon footprint. They have also collaborated with a well-known food delivery platform. In the future, restaurant operators will use PackAge+ circular packaging instead of plastic bags for food packaging.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"/en/storage/app/media/uploaded-files/1681800427881.jpeg\" alt=\"葉德偉_配客嘉執行長_2021_11_08_蔡仁譯攝-2.jpg\" class=\"fr-fic fr-dii\" data-result=\"success\" style=\"width: 900px;\"></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ye De Wei also revealed that PackAge+ is collecting various data points from the circular system to build an AI model that calculates the best recycling route. /Photograph : 蔡仁譯攝</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The investors of this funding round include CTBC Venture Capital, Chang Hua Commercial Bank Venture Capital, National Development Fund, Arbor Impact Investment, SIC Sustainable Impact Capital, Shell Amplify, and other strategic investors.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>According to the Environmental Protection Administration, Taiwan\'s e-commerce industry uses more than 220 million disposable packages annually, equivalent to producing over 50,000 tons of garbage and causing serious environmental impacts. In order to reduce packaging waste from the source, the \"E-commerce Packaging Reduction Regulations\" will be implemented on July 1, 2023. The regulations set targets for the use of circular packaging for businesses with capital over NT$150 million. By 2026, the circular packaging utilization rate should reach 15%, including the four major e-commerce companies MOMO, Eastern Home Shopping &amp; Leisure, PChome, and Shopee, as well as B2C businesses such as food, cosmetics, 3C products, and clothing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>PackAge+’s “circulating packaging” product can be reused at least 50 times and effectively reduce the waste of disposable packaging when shopping on e-commerce platforms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It can reduce around 1.2kg of carbon emissions using PackAge+’s packaging every time. However, besides the durable eco-friendly packaging, the key to the service is how to establish a perfect circular system from shipping, returning, to recycling and cleaning of the packaging bags.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"/en/storage/app/media/uploaded-files/1681800458122.jpeg\" alt=\"PackAge+ 配客嘉\" class=\"fr-fic fr-dii\" data-result=\"success\" style=\"width: 900px;\"></p>\r\n\r\n<p>PackAge+’s “circulating packaging” product can be reused at least 50 times and effectively reduce the waste of disposable packaging when shopping on e-commerce platforms. / Photograph : 配客嘉 提供</p>\r\n\r\n<p>PackAge+ has connected e-commerce platforms, return merchants, and consumers, using the cooperation of e-commerce platforms or return merchants\' coupons as a reward for consumers to return packaging. At the same time, it has connected e-commerce platforms and chain stores such as Shopee, Family Mart, and Carrefour. So far, there are 4,500 return stations and 650,000 circular packages in circulation, which is equivalent to reducing about 195,000 kilograms of disposable e-commerce packaging waste.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Collaborating with the semiconductor industry</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>In addition to its development in the circular economy and e-commerce fields, PackAge+ has also expanded into the technology industry. In 2023, PackAge+ collaborated with a well-known semiconductor wafer factory to develop \"Eco-Circular Boxes\" made from the factory\'s waste plastic, which will be used for logistics and transportation by their partner suppliers to create a more environmentally friendly supply chain.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Through this initiative, PackAge+ CEO Ye De Wei expressed his hope to collaborate with more technology manufacturers in the future. Besides using the waste plastic to create circular boxes for internal use, they will also provide these boxes to e-commerce platforms that sell relevant products.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For example, if a laptop brand sells well on a platform, then the laptop brand can produce its own circular box and provide it to customers through the platform, and it can reduce the brand\'s carbon emissions in the Scope 3 category.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Steve Lin, co-founder of SIC Sustainable Impact Investing, commented, \"Most companies today only focus on reducing greenhouse emissions in Scope 1 and Scope 2, but in reality, 80-95% of their emissions fall under Scope 3. We are optimistic about PackAge+’s multi-dimensional approach to help companies reduce their Scope 3 emissions, including using circular packaging for corporate gifts, circular box transportation in the supply chain, and other emerging services to become a driving force for companies to significantly reduce their emissions.\"</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The partner of Chang Hua Commercial Bank Venture Capital, also mentioned that PackAge+ can outsource the cleaning work in their circular packaging system to social welfare units, creating more job opportunities for vulnerable groups and promoting sustainable and inclusive employment and social innovation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>〔Original :Meet Global〕\r\n	<br><a href=\"https://meet-global.bnext.com.tw/articles/view/47902\">https://meet-global.bnext.com.tw/articles/view/47902</a></p>', NULL, 1, '2023-04-18 06:50:56', '2023-09-25 13:40:00', NULL),
(559, 'Boosting recruitment and retention of international talent', '2023-05-02', '', '<p>Taiwan in recent years has been facing rising competition for foreign talent along with a brain drain of domestic professionals. To fill the talent and technology gap for industries, the government enacted the Act for the Recruitment and Employment of Foreign Professionals in February 2018, along with amendments to the act in October 2021, to further ease work and residency regulations and improve tax and social security benefits for overseas professionals who wish to work in Taiwan. Furthermore, the government set up a policy consultation platform in July 2021 to strengthen Taiwan\'s ability to recruit and retain the international talent required for the nation\'s \"five plus two\" innovative industries and the Six Core Strategic Industries. In January 2023, the Executive Yuan also approved draft amendments to the Immigration Act that would increase incentives for high-quality talent to come and stay in Taiwan, thus creating a friendlier and more effective environment for talent recruitment and retention.\r\n	<br>\r\n	<br><strong>Key actions</strong>\r\n	<br>■ <strong>Relaxing work and visa requirements:</strong> The government is issuing Employment Gold Cards (a four-in-one work permit, resident visa, alien resident certificate and reentry permit) and employment-seeking visas; graduates from the world\'s top universities are exempt from the work requirement of two years\' previous work experience; foreign professionals are exempt from applying for work permits once they have gained permanent residency; and the maximum duration of a work permit for a foreign special professional has been increased to five years.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>■ <strong>Relaxing residency requirements:</strong> Foreign professionals, foreign special professionals, and foreign or overseas compatriot students may apply directly for a residency permit if they enter Taiwan visa-free or on a visitor visa, thus simplifying application procedures for working or studying in Taiwan. For foreign professionals applying for permanent residency, their required presence in Taiwan has been changed from a minimum of 183 days per year to an average of 183 days per year. For foreign special professionals applying for permanent residency, their required period of presence has been shortened from five years to three years. For foreigners who have obtained permanent residency, their required presence in Taiwan has been changed from a minimum of 183 days per year to an average of 183 days per year over the last five years.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>■ <strong>Improving tax incentives and social protections:&nbsp;</strong>Foreign special professionals coming to Taiwan for the first time will receive special tax exemptions for their first five years of employment, up from three years previously, and can qualify for expanded coverage under the national pension and national health insurance systems.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>■ <strong>Relaxing entry and residence restrictions for nationals without household registration:&nbsp;</strong>The required period of presence in Taiwan for nationals without household registration applying for permanent residency has been shortened to five years. The required presence for permanent residents applying for household registration has been shortened from one continuous year to 335 days within one year.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>■ <strong>Coordinating intragovernmental measures to recruit and retain talent:&nbsp;</strong>Policy strategies for international talent will focus on employment in the \"five plus two\" innovative industries, Six Core Strategic Industries and key service industries; strengthen recruitment and retention of personnel such as those demanded by large-scale investment companies, or graduates from the 500 top-ranked universities worldwide; and resolve various issues that professionals face when moving to Taiwan, thus building a better life for foreigners on the island.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>More information:\r\n	<br><a href=\"https://law.moj.gov.tw/ENG/LawClass/LawAll.aspx?pcode=A0030295\">Act for the Recruitment and Employment of Foreign Professionals</a>\r\n	<br><a href=\"https://law.moea.gov.tw/EngLawContent.aspx?lan=E&amp;id=10449\">Foreign Special Professionals with Specialized Knowledge/Skills in Economic Fields</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>〔Original : Executive Yuan 〕\r\n	<a href=\"https://english.ey.gov.tw/News3/9E5540D592A5FECD/440b0844-c16b-4d7f-98c6-f112cf0d493f\"></a>\r\n	<br><a href=\"https://english.ey.gov.tw/News3/9E5540D592A5FECD/440b0844-c16b-4d7f-98c6-f112cf0d493f\">https://english.ey.gov.tw/News3/9E5540D592A5FECD/440b0844-c16b-4d7f-98c6-f112cf0d493f</a></p>', NULL, 1, '2023-05-02 09:15:34', '2023-05-02 09:18:30', NULL),
(560, 'The Invitation of Tech Innovation Excellence Award with the Highest Prize 30,000USD', '2023-05-04', '', '<div dir=\"auto\">The “Tech Innovation Excellence Award (<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/hashtag/tieaward?__eep__=6&amp;__cft__[0]=AZXB126NGnoCf-U9BohCA5A-zzWYeNz1jKbf1xyCCTtsyShUtXHzZZCSmWi-S3lv_aJNKgasdAH1kD3HIxv7uBbM8gN9hHbYPCE5_YP34UIf6TTyU3kz9VzLi8ZoUBp9jkhj9Yk4VlGQHr4apGxOC2F4X90y8h5v7H7pdCmbibK72o-KPclI1gHNV8SUoIB0_yw&amp;__tn__=*NK-R\" tabindex=\"0\">#TIEAward</a>)” is a contest co-organized by Taiwan’s National Science and Technology Council (NSTC) and other Taiwanese governments.</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">&nbsp;In 2023, the TIE Award will expand application eligibility under two themes, “Smart Innovation for Semiconductor” and “Technologies for Net-Zero Emissions.”</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">Winners of the TIE Award will receive opportunities to partner with Taiwan’s top semiconductor companies</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">The prizes for the winning teams on each topic:</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">-1st Place: USD 30,000</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">-2nd Place: USD 20,000</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">-3rd Place: USD 10,000</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">-3 Honorable mentions: USD 7,000 each</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">\r\n	<br>\r\n</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">Winning teams from overseas will receive partial subsidies for flight tickets and accommodation. &nbsp;</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">Coworking space in Taiwan Tech Arena - TTA 臺灣科技新創基地 (<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/hashtag/tta?__eep__=6&amp;__cft__[0]=AZXB126NGnoCf-U9BohCA5A-zzWYeNz1jKbf1xyCCTtsyShUtXHzZZCSmWi-S3lv_aJNKgasdAH1kD3HIxv7uBbM8gN9hHbYPCE5_YP34UIf6TTyU3kz9VzLi8ZoUBp9jkhj9Yk4VlGQHr4apGxOC2F4X90y8h5v7H7pdCmbibK72o-KPclI1gHNV8SUoIB0_yw&amp;__tn__=*NK-R\" tabindex=\"0\">#TTA</a>)</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">Submission Deadline: May 31, 2023</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">Learn more and register: <a href=\"https://reurl.cc/n726lX?fbclid=IwAR0RsEp2Jb6DBv9zBEK01YmxrJszBUTG_ChBza-jXHldAwfjyZR5WeG_GAY\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" tabindex=\"0\" target=\"_blank\">https://reurl.cc/n726lX</a></div>', NULL, 1, '2023-05-08 06:27:07', '2023-05-08 06:27:07', NULL),
(561, 'Startup Innovation STARTUP your iMAGINATION!', '2023-05-15', '', '<div dir=\"auto\">Startup Innovation STARTUP your iMAGINATION!</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">Upcoming event. Date: 2023/5/30-6/2</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">\r\n	<br>\r\n</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">SMEA of MOEA will join InnoVEX2023! Startup Terrace Linkou, Startup Terrace Kaohsiung, A2T, IAPS, and Hsinchu Biomedical Science Park Hospital cooperated together in the SMEA pavilion and held numerous events to sparkle InnoVEX. To bring the topics related to Smart Life &amp; Business, Future Intelligence, Smart Manufacturing, Green Tech, and Smart Healthcare the innovative solutions in the SMEA pavilion just nearby your side.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">\r\n	<br>\r\n</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">【SMEA InnoVEX2023 - Startup Innovation】</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">Date: May 30th (Tue.) – June 2nd (Fri.), 2023</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">Topic: STARTUP your iMAGINATION!</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">Location: TaiNex 2, 1F, Q0223a</div>', NULL, 1, '2023-05-16 08:59:41', '2023-05-16 08:59:50', NULL),
(562, 'K-STARTUP GRAND CHALLENGE 2023 - THE GOLDEN GATE FOR STARTUPS TO EXPAND INTO ASIA', '2023-05-10', '', '<div dir=\"auto\">K-Startup Grand Challenge 2023 is now open for promising startups looking to expand into Asia using the Korean market as a stepping stone.</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">K-Startup Grand Challenge held annually by the Korean Government since 2016. With 2,653 global startups applied from 122 countries for KSGC 2022, the program has resulted in 167 startups setting up bases in Korea.</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">This is not just a competition, it\'s a gateway to Asia!</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">Grants for Top 10 Startups&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">- 1st Prize: $120.000</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">- 2nd Prize: $70.000</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">- 3rd Prize: $40.000</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">- 4th Prize: $25.000</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">- 5th Prize: $15.000</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">\r\n	<br>\r\n</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">More than just a competition, KSGC 2023 is a door for Startups to expand to foreign markets, connect with leading corporate and VCs in Asia, and validate their business model.</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">Apply now and become the winner of the next success story!! &nbsp;</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">Application Period: April 10th – May 18th, 2023.</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">Apply now ► <a href=\"https://www.k-startupgc.org/?fbclid=IwAR2OivnLip9GsTNXzL5BLRHTXbP8iFXOXFnTkY8XxIKVsUq4ZdesYM0siec\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" tabindex=\"0\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.k-startupgc.org/</a></div>', NULL, 1, '2023-05-16 09:01:16', '2023-05-16 09:01:16', NULL),
(563, 'The Intelligent Future of Food', '2023-05-11', '', '<p><strong><em>A handful of Taiwanese entrepreneurs are paving the way forward through a combination of technology and innovation, changing the game for everything from production to delivery.</em></strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There’s a buzz of activity inside Taipei Tech Arena, a sports facility partially repurposed into a startup hub, providing first-class office amenities like well-proportioned conference rooms and presentation areas, desks, co-working spaces, and the IT infrastructure needed to launch entrepreneurial dreams.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Inside sits Foodland Ventures, a Taiwan-based Agritech venture capital firm and accelerator dedicated to F&amp;B innovations and farm-to-table solutions. The company believes opportunities in this sector are often overlooked by bigger venture capital funds.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>“Taiwan is very strong in technology as well as agriculture,” says Foodland Ventures CEO Victor Chen. “We hope to marry these two skills and bring this to other markets. Taiwan has so many tech talents and a robust farm-to-table system, with many good entrepreneurs who can propose solutions to current problems.”</p>\r\n\r\n<p>One lesson learned by the F&amp;B industry during the pandemic is that restaurants need to be more than physical locations. Most restaurants extended their business well beyond the walls of their dining rooms through delivery service and take-out. In fact, 65% of Taiwan’s restaurants still offer food delivery. Many successful eateries have also developed a “brand,” easily identifiable on the internet and attracting online orders that bolster revenues.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Chen posits that a strong brand creates the opportunity for expansion abroad, pointing to the popularity of new Taiwanese franchises in the U.S., such as 85°C Bakery Cafe, Din Tai Fung, and numerous bubble tea shops. These companies perfected their business model in Taiwan before going overseas.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>“Taiwan is good at standardizing practices and making food accessible through low prices or what is referred to as CP (cost-performance) value,” says Chen. “Taiwan is also a small geographic area, leading to innovation and quick adaptation to market trends.”</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Currently, many of the abovementioned businesses are also implementing new technology. For instance, Din Tai Fung uses a QR code to direct patrons to an ordering platform with assistance provided by waitstaff.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>“This form of digital ordering offers better sanitation, as you aren’t touching a common menu anymore,” says Chen. “It’s also better than a shared menu tablet, which needs to be cleaned after each use.” He adds that such orders can be linked to a delivery robot, which can also lead to reduced staffing costs. “Restaurants spend a lot of money when it comes to training new personnel,” he says, stressing the significant time required to teach cash register systems, order delivery processes, and other tasks.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Eliminating such training through online menus and digital payment can lead to big savings. In fact, one Foodland-invested company, DotDot Global, provides an online ordering system where participating restaurants are given printer boxes that print new order tickets. The system even collects payments, eliminating many front-of-house functions and allowing local business owners to compete directly with Uber Eats and Foodpanda.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Another Foodland investee, Kabob, offers platform-level management of digital menus, online ordering, and inventory and account management. With just a few simple clicks, menus, signage, and displays can be updated to reflect new prices or add new menu items.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>“To change the menu in a store or throughout the entire network takes less training and manpower now,” says Chen. “It is all interconnected digital signage and digital ordering. We want to offer SaaS [Software as a Service] solutions that are modularized and interconnected, and all based upon software and computer technology.”</p>\r\n<figure><img src=\"/storage/app/media/uploaded-files/1684228000178.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"401\" srcset=\"https://topics.amcham.com.tw/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/IF14-1.jpg 800w, https://topics.amcham.com.tw/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/IF14-1-300x200.jpg 300w, https://topics.amcham.com.tw/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/IF14-1-768x513.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" class=\"fr-fic fr-dii\" data-result=\"success\">\r\n	<figcaption><strong><em>Space Bao uses plant-based meat substitutes to break stereotypes of traditional and vegetarian food.</em></strong></figcaption>\r\n</figure>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Innovations at the source</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>While many food businesses benefit from innovations, they also face challenges from the impact of climate change. Drought-like conditions have already displaced rice planting in central and southern Taiwan this year, and other agricultural industries may also be affected as climate change exacerbates extreme weather.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Taiwan’s aquaculture industry is now suffering from seasonality, or differing temperate conditions, which can affect the growth of fish, shrimp, and mollusks. Chen says neighboring Southeast Asia is faring better, as it’s not only more competitive in terms of weather but also labor costs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Foodland’s biggest investment success is ID Water, which uses IOP sensors to test water quality for shrimp breeding pools. The company implements IoT solutions such as underwater cameras, sensors, and other equipment for real-time monitoring to solve water quality problems.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After developing a simple and cost-effective solution to maintain ideal shrimp breeding conditions, ID Water was able to export its technology to Thailand. The technology also helps cut down on pesticides and chemicals once needed to keep shrimp ponds clean and free of dreaded parasites.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As many countries move toward intensive agricultural practices due to limited land availability, more parasites and disease will inevitably affect crops and livestock. This problem is especially prevalent in Taiwan.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>“We have lots of biodiversity because of our year-round temperate climate, but this also leads to a lot of pests,” says Chen. “There are many pests that need to be controlled throughout the year. Many entrepreneurs are trying to pinpoint how to combat these pests in an economical way.”</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Many are turning to technology and automation to help battle the problem. Technological solutions also help alleviate shortages caused by skyrocketing labor costs and a decreased interest in physically demanding agricultural work.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>“One entrepreneur notified us that there is now a shortage of drone pilots,” notes Chen. “They are highly in demand in the agriculture sector, which is now using drones to apply pesticides. Traditional applications – a person spraying a field, for example – wastes 70-80% of pesticides as they are blown away by the wind. “With drones, downward wind caused by propellers allows for a more efficient application of pesticides.”</p>\r\n<figure><img src=\"/storage/app/media/uploaded-files/1684228027610.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"400\" srcset=\"https://topics.amcham.com.tw/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/IF1-1.jpg 800w, https://topics.amcham.com.tw/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/IF1-1-300x200.jpg 300w, https://topics.amcham.com.tw/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/IF1-1-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" class=\"fr-fic fr-dii\" data-result=\"success\">\r\n	<figcaption><em><strong>Lypid showcased its latest innovation, the world’s first plant-based “pork belly” at the 2023 Consumer Electronics Show, held January in Las Vegas.</strong></em></figcaption>\r\n</figure>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>New, flavorful experiences</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Across from Yongkang Park in central Taipei sits a sleek, futuristic restaurant with a new take on dining. At Space Bao, the ingredients are just as futuristic as the ordering and payment methods, which are done on a large touchscreen monitor at the front of the store.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Space Bao has already won over many netizens eager to gain a glimpse of future dining experiences. The restaurant serves vegetarian food with a modern twist on traditional pan-fried buns. Space Bao’s buns are made from a meat alternative infused with PhytoFat, a source of plant-derived fat, and available in innovative new flavors, including corn soup and Szechuan pepper.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Alternative protein is a growing segment that’s gained considerable hype for being healthier and having a smaller impact on the environment. One company that’s gained from the increased interest is Lypid, a Taiwanese startup focused on driving innovation in the food industry and the creator of PhytoFat.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As a self-proclaimed “foodie, food addict, and avid cook,” Lypid co-founder Michelle Lee is passionate about making a difference through her work in food innovation. Her goal is to have a positive impact on the world by creating new and exciting food products that push the boundaries of what’s possible.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Lee has dedicated much of her life to food science, first joining National Taiwan University’s Food Science Department before attending Ohio State University and then earning a Ph.D. at Cornell University. She later went to work for heavyweights in the food industry, such as Nescafé and Nestlé. Her specialization in micro-encapsulation technology, which she says is “basically adding a coating to fats so they don’t dissolve easily, increasing bioavailability of active ingredients,” inspired her to create PhytoFat.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Previous incarnations of plant-based meats used coconut oil, which melts and leaks out of the product easily. Lee’s innovation mimics real animal tissue and helps plant-based meat retain fat throughout the cooking process. Her innovations aim to make vegetarian foods on par with – if not tastier than – meat dishes like hamburger patties or high-quality steaks.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>“At the moment, about 40% of a burger is fat,” she says. “This has been overlooked in many plant-based meats. Our solution is PhytoFat, which is like animal tissue and has better flavor delivery with 33% less calories and zero cholesterol.”</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Lee’s work earned her an invitation to the UN’s COP27 climate conference, where she delivered a speech about how food production contributes to climate change. Around 30% of global carbon emissions, water use, and land use are associated with food production. Greening this production chain can bring great benefits to everyone, she stresses.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Lee believes there’s a big market for her innovation. Alternative meat represents only 2% of the sliced meat market, and Lee notes a substantial potential for growth, especially due to the contributions of flexitarians who eat meat but prefer plant-based items.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>“We are working with Louisa Coffee and their 500-plus stores, which offer six different products and flavors,” she says. “This partnership is growing and has inspired us to offer other products that target Asian cuisine, like steamed buns.” Lee’s company is already working on making the world’s first plant-based pork belly.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Another business using technology to cater to consumer needs is Bean Friends Forever (bff), co-founded by Samson Huang. His company is a coffee subscription service that predicts a customer’s taste profile through an introductory questionnaire.</p>\r\n<figure>\r\n	<br><img src=\"/storage/app/media/uploaded-files/1684228065637.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"402\" height=\"600\" srcset=\"https://topics.amcham.com.tw/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/IF3-1.jpg 536w, https://topics.amcham.com.tw/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/IF3-1-201x300.jpg 201w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 402px) 100vw, 402px\" class=\"fr-fic fr-dii\" data-result=\"success\"></figure>\r\n\r\n<p>“Our questionnaire is the secret sauce for our business,” says Huang. He says that asking just six questions can accurately predict what type of coffee a customer likes. Anything more can be overkill, and fewer questions would make customers feel the quiz is too superficial.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The questions asked by bff are quite common, even bordering on banal. They include “where do you shop,” “what desserts do you like,” “what kind of coffee flavor do you like,” and “where do you buy coffee?” As it turns out, these questions have a statistical significance that can help predict a person’s flavor profile.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After answering the questions and receiving a personalized flavor profile, customers are invited to purchase an initial shipment of single-use drip coffee packets for around NT$420 (US$12). Flavor notes and reviews from local baristas are attached to the packaging.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Bff currently has 1,000 subscribers after doubling in 2022. Aside from individual customers, the company also services offices and restaurants. “We don’t have a membership fee as we are totally based on frequency of orders,” says Huang. “Typically, a customer gets a new order every six weeks. Sometimes the contents are like a mystery box as they don’t know beforehand what’s inside.”</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Huang attributes some of the company’s success to its collaborations with numerous independent roasters, including those who roast in small quantities and want to impart their extensive knowledge of coffee to friends and fellow baristas. “We often sell our coffee to high-end restaurants, who appreciate our quality because the coffee at the end of the meal has to be quite good,” he adds.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Huang doesn’t operate a physical store. He attends fairs and uses Google ads and search engine optimization to promote his business. So far his team is quite small, with fewer than 10 people actively promoting the company on social media and its website by sharing a few stories each week. Huang believes his highly focused, niche business model, which allows consumers to access exactly what they want at a competitive price, will play a prominent role in the future of retail.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>〔The original article: <a href=\"https://topics.amcham.com.tw/2023/04/the-intelligent-future-of-food/\">https://topics.amcham.com.tw/2023/04/the-intelligent-future-of-food/</a>&nbsp;〕</p>', NULL, 1, '2023-05-16 09:11:41', '2023-05-16 09:11:41', NULL);
INSERT INTO `ip_ieit_news` (`id`, `title`, `art_date`, `tag`, `content`, `pic`, `enabled`, `created_at`, `updated_at`, `deleted_at`) VALUES
(564, '2023 H.Spectrum+ Accelerator Healthy Phoenix Programme . Apply Now!', '2023-05-17', 'startup', '<div dir=\"auto\">CrossBond, a certified national entrepreneurship incubator is honored to serve as the international partner for the Southeast Asian and Indian markets in this 2023 H.Spectrum+ &nbsp;Accelerator Healthy Phoenix Programme with Hon Hai Technology Group Foxconn Yonglin Foundation.</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">\r\n	<a tabindex=\"-1\"></a>Attention Southeast Asian and Indian healthcare and AIOT startups! Are you ready to take your business to the next level? Join the 2023 H.Spectrum+ Accelerator Healthy Phoenix Programme , held jointly by CrossBond and Foxconn, and gain access to a closed-loop platform designed to make your startup grow quickly as well as win the chance to get direct funding !&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">Our programme provides startups with strategy and tactics, venture capital, and assistance for prototype development and manufacturing cost reduction. We welcome startups from the healthcare industry, including biotech, medical equipment, functional medicine, AI for smart healthcare, and more.</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">But that\'s not all! This year, we are also opening our doors to medical school students, residents, visiting attending, and nurses whose backgrounds are healthcare-related. If you have an amazing idea but haven\'t registered a company yet, we encourage you to submit your big idea or business plan right now!</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">2023 H.Spectrum+ is the largest global accelerator program welcoming international startups from all around the world ! &nbsp;We are excited to welcome startups from all over Southeast Asia to participate. So, don\'t miss out on this opportunity to take your healthcare startup to new heights. The registration period is only until the end of June 2023, so act fast!</div>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n	<br>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<div dir=\"auto\">Registration Time：2023/4/20~2023/6/30</div>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<div dir=\"auto\">Registration URL：https://forms.gle/o3qPMqZF6sGoCpKs8</div>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<div dir=\"auto\">Know more about 2023 H.Spectrum+ Accelerator Healthy Phoenix Programme ! https://youtu.be/ejXv5k04Pik</div>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<div dir=\"auto\">Notes for selection：https://reurl.cc/2WkdYE</div>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">If you have any questions, please contact us !</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">Email：info@crossbond.tw</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">Phone：+8862-5574-0032</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">Web&amp;Social Media：https://linktr.ee/crossbondofficial</div>', NULL, 1, '2023-05-17 07:18:52', '2023-05-17 07:20:21', NULL),
(565, '55688, the most competitive ride-hailing platform in Taiwan, transforms into a lifestyle services super app', '2023-05-30', '', '<blockquote>\r\n\r\n	<p>55688, the biggest and most popular ride-hailing platform in Taiwan, turned into a lifestyle-focused app. The credits go to its new CEO, Tracy Lin, the daughter of the previous CEO Tsun-Tien Lin. “Even though there are 6.8 million users on our platform, we haven’t fully created the value that this large user base could bring,” said Lin. As a result, Lin has been promoting the digital transformation inside 55688, turning it into a more lifestyle-focused app that includes more lifestyle services such as dry cleaning and housekeeping besides ride-hailing.</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<h2>What makes 55688 the most competitive ride-hailing platform in Taiwan?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"/en/storage/app/media/uploaded-files/1685426565180.jpeg\" alt=\"林念臻_台灣大車隊執行長\" class=\"fr-fic fr-dii\" data-result=\"success\" style=\"width: 900px;\"></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The credits of digital transformation go to its new CEO, Tracy Lin, the daughter of the previous CEO Tsun-Tien Lin. / Photograph : 蔡仁譯</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Even though more and more ride-hailing platforms such as Uber have operated in Taiwan, 55688 has always dominated the market with 24% market share and 80 million trips every year. One out of four taxis in Taiwan is from 55688, which is a formidable competitor in the field. “Uber entered Taiwan in 2013, however, the number of our drivers has been growing since then; In 2017, LINE TAXI also entered the market, but the number of taxi hailing tasks at 55688 has grown even faster.” said Lin.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Facing fierce competition in taxi business, as a traditional company with a long history, 55688 has been dedicated to digital transformation with ⅕ of its annual budget invested in the internal technology department. For instance, 29 digital payment options are available at 55688. The determination to transform drew the attention of Headline Asia, one of the biggest technology-focused VC headquartered in Tokyo.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In 2022, 55688 announced that Headline Asia had invested US$5M to help 55688 to expand more services for their 6.8 million users. “I can see a huge potential of 55688,” said the partner of Headline Asia Joseph Huang, “People only perceive 55688 as a ride-hailing platform, in fact, the app has become one of the best in lifestyle service sector and there is much more services closely related to users’ daily life that we can develop.”</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>The key to success - innovation - optimization of the ride-hailing process for drunk passengers and valentines</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"/en/storage/app/media/uploaded-files/1685426565230.jpeg\" alt=\"台灣大車隊APP\" class=\"fr-fic fr-dii\" data-result=\"success\" style=\"width: 900px;\"></p>\r\n\r\n<p>55688 is now a lifestyle-focused app that includes more services such as dry cleaning and housekeeping besides ride-hailing. / Photograph : 台灣大車隊</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As both the target audience and operator of 55688, Lin always pays attention to all the unmet customer needs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For instance, Lin once found that the page design of designated driving services is too complicated to understand, especially when people are tipsy, leading to the optimization of page design. Now, when we go to the page of designated driving services, the system will automatically propose the most likely options that a user would prefer by analyzing their data of user behaviors, simplifying and optimizing the process.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Besides, 55688 also launched a “life secretary” service before Valentine’s day, which was ideated by the marketing and e-commerce manager at 55688, Huei-Jhen Yang. Through this service, users can reserve a taxi with flowers and chocolate inside and decorated with customized photos and messages.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This special service provided only 10 seats, which were sold out immediately after the launch. Thanks to the huge success, 55688 is planning to offer more diverse services for different festivals and important moments in life.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>The key to success - audacity and decisiveness - launch new service in 1 day</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Last year (2022), China decided to stop importing fruits from Taiwan, causing severe and negative impact on fruit farmers in Taiwan.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The digital transformation consultant for fruit farmers in south Taiwan, Yao-Kuan Huang, was struggling to find the new buyers of the fruits that were supposed to be imported in China. In the depth of despair, he contacted Lin through the introduction by the secretary of the director of information office of Kaohsiung city.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After understanding the request, Lin agreed to help solve this problem and instantly organized a temporary team to support the fruit farmers. In less than a day, the fruits products were launched on 55688.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Moreover, Lin even provided coupons for ride-hailing to attract more customers to buy fruits, and the 1000 boxes of fruits were sold out in less than 10 days. This success totally impressed the fruit farmers and broke their stereotype for taxi apps like 55688.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>The key to success - thoughtfulness - drivers are the most important treasure</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"/en/storage/app/media/uploaded-files/1685426565267.jpeg\" alt=\"台灣大車隊\" class=\"fr-fic fr-dii\" data-result=\"success\" style=\"width: 900px;\"></p>\r\n\r\n<p>One of the most important business philosophies of 55688 from the previous CEO, Tsun-Tien Lin, is to care for their drivers. &nbsp;/ Photograph : 台灣大車隊提供</p>\r\n\r\n<p>According to the observation from the partner of Headline Asia, Joseph Huang, what makes 55688 outstanding among all the ride-hailing platforms is their care for the drivers. This is also one of the most important business philosophies of 55688 from the previous CEO, Tsun-Tien Lin.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As the frontline of business, drivers’ strongly influences users’ opinons. As a result, 55688 firmly believe that they have to take good care of the drivers before taking care of users. 55688 thus provides not only a wide range of services for drivers such as repairing and car-washing but also some rules such as uniforms and the tidiness in the car.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Aiming to become a super APP, 55688 has thrived to innovate.</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>In 2022, the annual revenue of 55688 increased by 24%, proving the ability and potential of the new young CEO. “However, we’ve only utilized 5% of the potential values brought from our large user base,” said Lin.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Lin therefore aims to turn 55688 into a super APP, which provides various lifestyle services such as cleaning and moving. However, how to cooperate with the laborers who are not familiar with digital service and how to provide a consistent and standardized service to customers would be a challenge for 55688, but at the same time, a huge opportunity.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>〔Original :Meet Global〕\r\n	<br><a href=\"https://meet-global.bnext.com.tw/articles/view/47920\">https://meet-global.bnext.com.tw/articles/view/47920</a></p>', NULL, 1, '2023-05-30 06:03:35', '2023-09-25 13:37:49', NULL),
(566, '[Startup Activity] What it takes to be a leader', '2023-06-09', '', '<p>Girls in Tech Taiwan and AIT are inviting a speaker from the U.S. Speaker Program of the Department of State to come to Taiwan. Nancy Hayes is a wonderful leader in the business world, and specializes in leadership development. People are at the core of leadership. It\'s often the most difficult yet rewarding part of a business. What are the keys to great leadership? And how can we train ourselves to be a successful leader? Let\'s dive in!</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Date : 6pm - 8pm, June 27th</li>\r\n	<li>Venue : American Innovation Center (美國創新中心)</li>\r\n	<li>Format : 30 minutes sharing from speaker follow by 1 hour QA/ conversation</li>\r\n	<li>Cost : FREE!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>About the speaker:\r\n	<br>Nancy Hayes is an angel investor, advisor to women entrepreneurs and an executive coach. She focuses on entrepreneurship and management/leadership and has a portfolio of angel investments in more than 30 women-led companies. She regularly consults on leadership, career and organizational effectiveness, with a special emphasis on coaching women executives. Prior to this role she served as senior executive in a Fortune 5 corporation, CEO of 2 non-profit organizations, dean of a large college of business and CFO of a state university. In 2013, She was cofounder of a rewards-based crowdfunding site for women with small business called Moola Hoop.</p>', NULL, 1, '2023-06-15 02:19:31', '2023-06-15 02:19:31', NULL),
(567, 'InnoVEX2023 comes to an end.', '2023-06-09', '', '<div dir=\"auto\">During the InnoVEX 2023, The Startup Innovation, we have a large number of guests and invitations, which maximize the benefits and highlight our main idea: “STARTUP your iMAGINATION!”.</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">Focusing on startuptech, we bring the showcase with innovative technology to share with all the participants, trying to turn our imagination of the future into the real world.</div>', NULL, 1, '2023-06-15 02:23:44', '2023-06-15 02:23:44', NULL),
(568, 'Startup Odyssey: Taiwan & Austria as Next Destinations', '2023-06-15', '', '<p>A new business spot in Asia or Europe?&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Pin Taiwan and Austria on your roadmap!&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;Lost in your adventure into Asian market? Startup Terrace will show you Taiwan’s all-around resources, including soft-landing program, entrepreneur visa, gold cards, and more, to build strong business and networks!&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Set your foot on Europe from Austria! GIN Austria will be your guide to discover potential clients and relevant stakeholders or set up a European base in the most central European country with its emerging capital Vienna.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sign up NOW to get the meeting link. See you online on June. 30th!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>－Date: June 30th, 2023 &nbsp;\r\n	<br>－Time: 10:00-11:30 (Austria: GMT+2)/ 16:00-17:30 (Taiwan:GMT+8)\r\n	<br>－Register NOW: <a href=\"https://seminars.tca.org.tw/D10o03985.aspx\">https://seminars.tca.org.tw/D10o03985.aspx</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>(Meeting link will be emailed to you after registration.)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For more inquiries, please contact:\r\n	<br>Shaph Su (Startup Terrace) at shaph@mail.tca.org.tw or +886 2 2577 4249 ext.505 /\r\n	<br>Jan Arpe (GIN) at Jan.Arpe@ffg.at or +43 57755-1320</p>', NULL, 1, '2023-06-15 03:34:00', '2023-06-17 02:24:53', NULL),
(569, '2023 IP2Launchpad IP2Scaleout Program is officially Sailing now!', '2023-06-12', '', '<div dir=\"auto\">The IP² Scale Out program jointly organized by the SOSA Accelerator in Israel, has selected 5 Taiwanese startups at the end of March, after six weeks of virtual program training, the second phase of the New York landing has started in June to carry out international business opportunities and investment activities. &nbsp;Let’s introducing the 5 outstanding IP2 Scaleout Teams:\r\n	<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/hashtag/authme?__eep__=6&amp;__cft__[0]=AZVbevDfO_LCdvkwYoM3Dc9mwTbFtgYFFpLEJQvuBTJg0SoLQZLbnMaHwJWM0Lg718VbtC8CNugCnPSzjah76n3g4jPTc3Ml_woCe1pj_z54q4Oj-UDz6Fw3DaI_DYvp2Sb-8wWSBvVTnVHipJgCoh20bV-EGX5adlAxaHAI0tlmUp4-_qQagUJnunaadihfgBU&amp;__tn__=*NK-R\" tabindex=\"0\"></a>\r\n	<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\"><strong>AuthMe</strong></div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">Identity verification solutions that utilize advanced AI and ML technologies to help corporates verify user identities, using an innovative eKYC solution to decrease identity fraud in digital verification.</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">See more: <a href=\"https://shorturl.at/lmu46?fbclid=IwAR13uTu3J-8yvYWokmmb-x5gtb5549actxSGUjDMedWHdYqVpBmWYp9lVow\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\" tabindex=\"0\" target=\"_blank\">https://shorturl.at/lmu46</a></div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">\r\n	<br><strong>Canner</strong></div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">Data solution by providing a all-in-one platform for querying and analyzing information across multiple databases, file systems, and format. Targeting B2B model in enterprise use cases in the finance, manufacturing, and retail industries.</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">See more: <a href=\"https://shorturl.at/aD569?fbclid=IwAR0e7GfV6wSMyanT97xPeYekUGQ7YYHE-RbGmJQkWA996hS7tNSfdR_K35o\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\" tabindex=\"0\" target=\"_blank\">https://shorturl.at/aD569</a></div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">\r\n	<br><strong>DeepWave</strong></div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">Mainly focus on developing AI natural semantics (NLU) and AIaaS (AI as a service) cloud intelligence (cloud brain) of text analysis engine, and provide application solutions of human intelligence and artificial intelligence hybrid collaborative technology in vertical fields.</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">See more: <a href=\"https://shorturl.at/begsG?fbclid=IwAR2JmrE9YHZXlxWVk6sxvJtZWg7apd4mqz8uAyqQ-7_MMXfgpGmaADJQTLs\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\" tabindex=\"0\" target=\"_blank\">https://shorturl.at/begsG</a></div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">\r\n	<br><strong>Frontierco</strong><strong>ol</strong></div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">B2B SaaS solution for providers in the fashion, footwear, and textile industry, creating 3D-ready materials and AI-enhanced technology to create faster time to market for producers.</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">See more: <a href=\"https://shorturl.at/FGIPT?fbclid=IwAR0yuqy9hdQ4YijvXOwXHGhvlqdBErlSDx6dxQYtu_EoxBpTJKOpIAQP5fI\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\" tabindex=\"0\" target=\"_blank\">https://shorturl.at/FGIPT</a></div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">\r\n	<br><strong>ioNetworks</strong></div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">DL technology to provide video management platforms, AI video analytics, sensor identification solutions, and AI algorithm IP. Embedding AI in chips, reducing cost and time.</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">See more: <a href=\"https://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Freurl.cc%2FGAdoa3%3Ffbclid%3DIwAR2jYE3vcTIPIr6ihCcu0WlX0xlyBFCW41bvWqTiburX_np1ofL0CmiQr2g&amp;h=AT1ARzR1tyy5yIf7-RRc_QkjvzC1otvxBMaNq7dHOp_OevhRo_hM9pu0snlzmVkDPBqhYRy55CpQnsdyPEuOMeRNbxOOTy5RIxIcY5MLG-RxwDVQ7BkYE-NQD2SXowPkYYIP&amp;__tn__=-UK-R&amp;c[0]=AT3StnQWAcO9JsiJBlNwbG8abBWI7c3cFCA5oQjCEXBOZY41ujCWuwTSnOaCZI-t_-Rtgp9z3SZx5GHv1P7Fmgg97CJsKeiIcF_7E2-Wt081r1KU_sZ3D3m36bzwFD6fYzf_B8YwyIkz6sRvB2uMYDTG3wvUfnz0vtYKFKfrxiT8uxhLmNG5uPWnvIyfpmMJJj5dvm_lCeUj\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\" tabindex=\"0\" target=\"_blank\">https://reurl.cc/GAdoa3</a></div>', NULL, 1, '2023-06-15 03:37:34', '2023-06-15 03:37:34', NULL),
(570, '2023 A2T – Access to Taiwan Program Batch 2 SIGN UP NOW', '2023-06-17', '', '<p>A2T Program is a market access sprint program specifically designed for non-Taiwanese Tech startups to engage the Taiwan startup ecosystem. The program is a great opportunity for overseas startups to access Taiwan’s manufacturing, R&amp;D, and traditional high-tech industries and our deep tech talent pool.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Who we are looking for</strong>：\r\n	<br>-Non-Taiwanese Tech Startups\r\n	<br>-Asia Market Ready\r\n	<br>-Targeting Taiwan’s Manufacturing, R&amp;D, and hardware-software integration expertise</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Admission Period</strong>: May 22nd – June 25th</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Apply HERE</strong>: <a href=\"https://forms.gle/RhnAWozuhe84xvpEA\">https://forms.gle/RhnAWozuhe84xvpEA</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Learn more</strong>: <a href=\"https://iaps.ord.nycu.edu.tw/get-involved/startups/access-to-taiwan-a2t-program/\">https://iaps.ord.nycu.edu.tw/get-involved/startups/access-to-taiwan-a2t-program/</a></p>', NULL, 1, '2023-06-17 02:21:21', '2023-06-17 02:21:21', NULL),
(571, 'GO Malaysia Program Now Calling for Taiwan startups!', '2023-06-17', '', '<div dir=\"auto\">Startup Terrace is leading a Taiwan startup delegation to Malaysia this year! Let\'s fly and explore the market together! APPLY NOW for limited seats!&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">With an aim to expanding Taiwan startup businesses into Southeast Asia markets, Startup Terrace will select 5 excellent startups on the mission to Malaysia for a short landing program. There will be online training workshops, one-on-one mentoring, matchmakings, business visits and networking events. To maximize your international exposure, we will also participate in iconic local events – Selangor Smart City and Digital Economy Convention.</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">The selected teams can enjoy the subsidy for #light tickets, accommodation and office space!</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">\r\n	<br>\r\n</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">Qualifications:</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">Startup teams, according to SMEA, refer to the companies registered in Taiwan within 8 years, and the industries of Green Tech, ICT Industry, Smart Agriculture and E-Commerce Industry are preferred.</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">The application is open until Aug. 8th.</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">Apply now: <a href=\"https://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Flnkd.in%2FdvyBKuzh%3Ffbclid%3DIwAR3Ju-2iago87l7Q60oWAW1-MdGqtPhjsjZEg4uUiPQ3c7lGmTnDvZ6Yudc&amp;h=AT0l09_Qanp0rPyKWRogi9NYWZh_0Uh0WMPrC73BRRegg5Dx1QGwDlBBOtLf9etz-GwdvgPNW5mYM-h5dZxjAY1tlW8hKO3_o0YcIzMqVAay79nE8MP1qFfmSb3GGmBjwB-C&amp;__tn__=-UK-R&amp;c[0]=AT1VznK-yKKGV4ouq85hlUKweEWV6CyyK5LRP_n-DYcXyCPr7_ARPDJoNX4if0NL_d74J8ZtjbZ_iS6xovag5MJLldlnY3zXgvvWskB_L69OLlyo1Mt2uM1xXjvJQtiztMEpIUooj971noWruj70kzFA0dcssAbjRhbQ-qT5TJjFYaThjw\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\" tabindex=\"0\" target=\"_blank\">https://lnkd.in/dvyBKuzh</a></div>', NULL, 1, '2023-06-17 02:39:23', '2023-06-17 02:39:23', NULL),
(572, 'Awarded Forbes Asia 30 Under 30 entrepreneur builds pet care platform attracting 60,000+ pet parents', '2023-06-20', '', '<blockquote>\r\n\r\n	<p>Fluv, the visionary pet-sitting platform founded by Candace Chen, has become Taiwan\'s guardian angel for furry friends. With a surge in pet ownership, the demand for reliable pet care has soared. Fluv fills this void across Asia with its innovative online matchmaking services. Recognized for its excellence, Fluv proudly secured a spot on Forbes\' Asia 30 Under 30 list.</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p>More and more Taiwanese are keeping furry friends at home. Hence, pet sitting is becoming a pain point for many owners. Imagine white collars that live alone and keep pets. What are they to do when a week-long business trip comes up? Surely, they will be on tenterhooks if no one was there to look after their furry friends.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Such a dilemma caught the eye of Candace Chen, the co-founder and CEO of Fluv. When Chen was in the U.S., she had access to a U.S. pet-sitting platform. After she returned to Taiwan, she couldn\'t find similar services. To close the gap, Chen founded Fluv, a well-loved pet-sitting platform.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>“I have first-hand experience with the hassles of finding the right pet-sitting services. Plus, I\'ve seen similar platforms overseas, so I decided to meet up with the team,\" said Chen Lijun, the Angel Investor of Fluv, director of B Current Impact Investment, and former VP of Finance at IBM Taiwan.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Fluv specializes in online pet care matchmaking services. Chen pointed out that \"the market size of Taiwan is approximately US$716,000 (NT$22M), on par with Singapore. The Japanese market is 20 times bigger.” Clearly, the demand for pet sitting in Asia has not yet been satisfied.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In May 2023, Forbes released its annual report of Asia 30 Under 30, awarding “300 young entrepreneurs, leaders, and trailblazers,” who exerted positive influence amid economic uncertainty. Among the list was Fluv, a proud Taiwan-based pet care platform provider.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"/en/storage/app/media/uploaded-files/1688460120856.jpeg\" alt=\"毛小愛\" class=\"fr-fic fr-dii\" data-result=\"success\" style=\"width: 900px;\"></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Fluv specializes in pet care services, using an online app to match pet owners with pet sitters. / Photograph : 毛小愛</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Strictly selected pet sitter and prompt report builds word of mouth</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Fluv currently provides an array of services catering to different animals, including birds, dogs, cats, rabbits, and rodents. Services include home care, boarding, pet walking, and grooming. Usually, cat owners will choose home care plans, while dog owners mainly opt for boarding services.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The app is like an Airbnb for pets – users can see the photos, prices, and animals that each pet sitter specializes in. Home care and pet walking services are provided for clients who are away; therefore, the most vital component is trust. Chen said, \"In order to build trust, we invested a great deal of effort in selecting nannies.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\"At first, many could not accept letting strangers into their houses,” said Chen. Fluv is very strict in the selection of pet sitters. Those who want to register on the platform must be experienced in animal care with no criminal record. Furthermore, they have to take online training and tests. Out of the initial 5,000 interviewees, only 1,500 passed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>While similar platforms may require nannies to take one or two photos only, Fluv nannies must take pictures of food consumed and medication taken, as well as photos that show pets playing. Furthermore, nannies are asked to monitor their feces. Clients may also rent pet cameras on the app. Much to the users’ liking, reviews of the sitter are offered, which further facilitated trust.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>With word of mouth, the number of Fluv users reached more than 60,000. Chen added that the major attraction of the platform is the safety net it offers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Within 3 days after services were provided, Fluv would hand out compensation if issues were to arise. Since Fluv services come with insurance, users are further incentivized. Fluv also strives to increase the remuneration for pet sitters. Investor Chen Lijun pointed out, \"It is also important that the nanny can fully dedicate to the platform.”</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Expected triple revenue growth</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>So far, the user retention rate of Fluv reached 50%. Chen also revealed that revenue in 2022 would exceed approximately US$325,000 (NT$10M). With border restrictions lifting and international travel booming, the demand for pet sitting is on the rise.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Revenue in 2023 is expected to triple. Fluv is ready to enter Singapore, \"where many single people keep pets,” analyzed Chen. Fluv has also approached pet sitter dispatch companies in Japan.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\"In Japan, this profession has long been in practice. The Japanese are willing to accept this idea. The biggest difference is they are used to making reservations for pet sitting services on the phone.” Accordingly, the focus of the expansion to Japan will be on digital transformation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Looking ahead, Chen announced the plan is to leverage big data for AI-powered pet consulting services. The data includes information on pet breed, gender, and age, which help owners solve their problems through online chatbots.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Fluv’s approach solved existing pain points. “Most veterinarians are conservative, which makes data difficult to collect. Furthermore, we pay extra attention to data privacy regulations,” said Chen. With AI, Fluv is bound to dole out more agile strategies.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>〔Original :Meet Global〕\r\n	<br><a href=\"https://meet-global.bnext.com.tw/articles/view/47925\">https://meet-global.bnext.com.tw/articles/view/47925</a></p>', NULL, 1, '2023-07-04 08:43:35', '2023-09-25 13:36:40', NULL),
(573, 'AmCham urges Taiwan to improve energy supplyment and talent retention', '2023-06-27', '', '<blockquote>\r\n\r\n	<p>In its 2023 Taiwan White Paper released on June 7, the American Chamber of Commerce in Taiwan (AmCham) called on the Taiwan government to act urgently to improve its business environment, especially in terms of stable supply of energy and talent attraction.</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p>“No time to waste,” emphasized Vincent Shih, chairperson of the AmCham in the press conference, “strengthening economic resilience will be the focus for Taiwan amid the tensions from national security issues.” Releasing Taiwan White Paper on June 7, AmCham urged the government to take advantage of the unprecedented international attention, support, and goodwill it currently enjoys to strengthen its economic relations with the United States.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"/en/storage/app/media/uploaded-files/1688460374837.jpeg\" alt=\"Amcham white paper\" class=\"fr-fic fr-dii\" data-result=\"success\" style=\"width: 900px;\"></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The American Chamber of Commerce in Taiwan (AmCham) called on the Taiwan government to act urgently to improve its business environment, especially in terms of stable supply of energy and talent attraction. /Photograph : AmCham</p>\r\n\r\n<p>“Within the current framework of energy, we need to put more efforts into satisfying the surging demand,” said Amy Chang, president of AmCham. The Chamber emphasized the need for quick and sustained action to ensure a stable energy supply and create a more satisfying work environment to attract and retain talent. The White Paper also called for stricter adherence to the 60-day public notice and comment period for new or revised regulations, increased funding for innovative healthcare treatments, and the adoption of international practice in tendering critical public infrastructure projects.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In the White Paper’s Messages to Washington, AmCham lauded the positive development of the U.S.-Taiwan Initiative on 21st-Century Trade. The Chamber urged the two governments to establish a clear roadmap on how agreements under the Initiative will be executed and then move forward to negotiate a comprehensive bilateral trade agreement. AmCham additionally encouraged the U.S. government to schedule routine visits to Taiwan by high-level U.S. government officials and continue efforts to promote Taiwan’s participation in relevant international organizations.\r\n	<br>In the face of global economic headwinds and cross-Strait uncertainty, a “business as usual” mindset will no longer suffice, the White Paper said. AmCham stressed the importance for Taiwan to heighten its efforts to eliminate trade barriers and improve the regulatory system to bolster Taiwan’s competitiveness. It also urged the Taiwan and U.S. governments to begin negotiations on a bilateral double taxation avoidance agreement to facilitate trade and two-way investment.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Noting that only eight of the 102 issues raised in the 2022 White Paper have been resolved, the Chamber expressed the hope of holding more frequent meetings between its committees and the relevant Taiwan government agencies in the coming year.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>At the press conference for the launch of this year’s White Paper, AmCham Taiwan thanked the National Development Council for its annual efforts in coordinating the government’s response to the Chamber’s recommendations, as well as the relevant government ministries and agencies for their cooperation in addressing challenging regulatory issues.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>〔Original :Meet Global〕\r\n	<br><a href=\"https://meet-global.bnext.com.tw/articles/view/47928\">https://meet-global.bnext.com.tw/articles/view/47928</a></p>', NULL, 1, '2023-07-04 08:47:34', '2023-09-25 13:36:21', NULL),
(574, 'Deloitte Tohmatsu Workshop - Overview of Tokyo Stock Exchange (TSE) & IPO guidance', '2023-07-06', '', '<p>&nbsp;Exciting News! Join us for the exclusive IPO Workshop hosted by Startup Island TAIWAN, where we invite Deloitte Tohmatsu to share their experience!&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>．Date: July 14, 2023\r\n	<br>．Time: 13:00-14:00 (Please join the meeting at 12:45)\r\n	<br>．Location: Online (A zoom link will be sent to you once you sign up)\r\n	<br>．Language: English\r\n	<br>．Sign up for free: <a href=\"https://www.accupass.com/event/2307040333568670082750?fbclid=IwAR1eObR9BXo7x2tWXfAYFgEP_9XNCn90Uluh4n6ERn6E8mPfqj0Hae2nFLU\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\" tabindex=\"0\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.accupass.com/event/2307040333568670082750</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>----------</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Are you ready to unlock the secrets of going public? Don\'t miss this opportunity to learn from industry experts and gain valuable insights into the world of Initial Public Offerings (IPOs) in Japan.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>．Key Workshop Highlights:\r\n	<br>．Step-by-step guidance on IPO process in Japan\r\n	<br>．Strategies to maximize investor interest\r\n	<br>．Legal and regulatory considerations\r\n	<br>．Case studies of successful IPOs\r\n	<br>．Q&amp;A with industry leaders</p>\r\n\r\n<p>----------</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Agenda | Taiwan Time (GMT+8)</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>13:00-13:03&nbsp;| Opening Remarks</li>\r\n	<li>13:03-13:13 | Overview of Tokyo Stock Exchange (TSE)</li>\r\n	<li>13:13-13:23 | Listing Procedures - Requirements, Listing Examinations, etc</li>\r\n	<li>13:23-13:33 | Introduction of Deloitte\'s Offerings - Related IPOs Offerings (Japan)</li>\r\n	<li>13:33-13:38 | Introduction&nbsp;of Deloitte\'s Offerings - Taiwan Offerings&nbsp;(Taiwan)</li>\r\n	<li>13:38-13:58 | Q&amp;A</li>\r\n	<li>13:58-14:00 | Closing</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>----------</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Speakers |&nbsp;Deloitte Tohmatsu</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Yasuhisa Kashiwaya (Senior Manager)</li>\r\n	<li>Keishi Kimura (Senior Manager)</li>\r\n	<li>Yijin Lu (Manager)</li>\r\n	<li>Shigeyasu Hayakawa (Senior Manager)&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Harry Huang (Partner)&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL, 1, '2023-07-10 07:34:41', '2023-07-10 07:34:41', NULL),
(575, 'Academy for Women Entrepreneurs Taiwan (AWE Taiwan) is soaring globally!', '2023-07-10', '', '<div dir=\"auto\">AWE Taiwan just held an amazing accelerator bootcamp from June 28-30! Support from MOEA and AIT, we kicked off the event in style!&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">This year, AWE Taiwan launched its first Accelerator Bootcamp, aiming to connect networks, enhance fundraising skills, and expand internationally. Our goals: fundraising, market expansion, and globalization.</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">Participants engaged in inspiring by keynote speech, panel discussion, workshops and Pitch Demo Day practice, boosting their business models, fundraising strategies, and market expansion during the 3 days accelerator bootcamp.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">Next up: 1-on-1 mentorship! We\'ve invited experts in startups, transformation, investment, and marketing, including past award winners, to guide our entrepreneurs. Together, we\'ll accelerate growth and empower Taiwanese women entrepreneurs to conquer the global market!&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">\r\n	<br>\r\n</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">For more information about AWE Taiwan: <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/AWEinTaiwan?__cft__[0]=AZWKJ1H2jotqrpwqGwAWcmDfSu8Ddgv2ouPB8rOeFvbGIUSZkbb9KhiVFNJ3LjR5hgUKKOUQ_OVD_9ACnjsQcsgzCnpJoLRMyt-nPlNKGTag-ZEMmeqilHO34XLGVt5aT9psNoZuvQUrZMDGkE6tv86CqEi4o7MCYf1G9iGNf-4Ms0htcMFBR1WjdBeBv_nYw3U&amp;__tn__=-]K-R\" tabindex=\"0\">https://www.facebook.com/AWEinTaiwan</a></div>', NULL, 1, '2023-07-10 07:46:46', '2023-07-10 07:46:46', NULL),
(576, 'Digital Economy Series- Digital & Cloud Resilience', '2023-07-19', '', '<div dir=\"auto\">American Spaces Digital Economy Series brings policymakers, industry experts, entrepreneurs, and academia together unpacking the intricate landscape of technology innovation and its challenges for entrepreneurs, young talents and individuals alike. This specific symposium aims to foster a comprehensive understanding of the emerging technologies, particularly cloud applications to booster digital resilience, at the same time facing regulatory challenges and next generation cybersecurity issues. Through insightful fireside chat and panel discussions, participants will gain valuable insights into the strategies for maintaining digital resilience in the face of disruptive events, the legal and regulatory hurdles to endorse cloud services, and the latest cybersecurity trends and countermeasures.</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">Join us for a thought-provoking symposium where we explore the complexities and opportunities in the world of cloud services and equip ourselves with the knowledge to navigate this ever-changing terrain successfully.</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">\r\n	<br>【Event Details】</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">．Date &amp; Time: 4 August 2023 10:00-12:15 a.m. (Registration starts at 9:30)</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">．Venue: NTU SPACE M (No. 4 Alley 1, Lane 10, Zhoushan Road, Taipei)</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">．The event will be held in English</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">．Registration link：<a href=\"https://www.surveycake.com/s/wWzGM?fbclid=IwAR2V8f7tNZ4hP77QxQVf1N2iUL7BXwEyyQBLYBU_Ovror_9t_QI3u-8csUQ\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\" tabindex=\"0\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.surveycake.com/s/wWzGM</a></div>', NULL, 1, '2023-07-21 02:11:01', '2023-07-21 02:11:01', NULL),
(577, 'Join us at the 【2023 Bio Asia-Taiwan】, the Asia Biotechnology Exhibition!', '2023-07-21', '', '<p>In this event, there will be 18 sessions of innovative technology presentations covering precision medicine, healthcare, and smart medical fields. The presentations will be given by our technology research and development teams, incubator center residents, and key industry players. Through physical networking activities, we aim to establish collaboration channels among academia, government, research, and industries, facilitate industry partnerships, accelerate the commercialization of developed technologies, and enhance the international influence of our country\'s biomedicine and biotechnology sector!</p>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">Event Information:</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">● Date: July 27 (Thursday) - July 30 (Sunday)</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">● Venue: Taipei Nangang Exhibition Center, Hall 1, 4th floor, Booth N604 - \"Research Achievements Poster Exhibition\"</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">● Date: July 28 (Friday) - 1:20 PM</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">● Venue: Taipei Nangang Exhibition Center, Hall 1, 5th floor, Room 500 - \"Technology Matchmaking Meeting\"</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">Register for the Matchmaking Meeting: <a href=\"https://expo.bioasiataiwan.com/eventSeminarDetail.asp?no=208&amp;fbclid=IwAR1Ea7ISA0EBszbPyoaxmTappW-0_fOuAYiixdt-SWIRJ3ve-TpbsYqGuqg\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\" tabindex=\"0\" target=\"_blank\">https://expo.bioasiataiwan.com/eventSeminarDetail.asp?no=208</a></div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">Matchmaking Meeting Live Stream Link:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3D6JFE9OZfkaU%26fbclid%3DIwAR3elzGiViBXS16AeNY2sAr0_XZtYktsLJ22zs-QFfzZgbIQbTvB-3SMfig&amp;h=AT3FjpM_ins-T2zwbkPgNQ9DkAA6LSeY4YzCdXqRCMVeicWWDDm1P1TYodhR_uZz5xmWVNyi8NGpALQJkSSeor__wiYVMUceW72jMS7QOjG8ZU3yOJHNYe4U3Ousr4e2Pluw&amp;__tn__=-UK-R&amp;c[0]=AT0-rkKhtP9_lmIGtTqibW0M45YJeI824nhX7Hqz9qIctLuFOFO9EdQazI-jAiCxNKwS09daeKbO2gmztyV3ukaaGmlwgschJ3IUJnYy55WYiQkJZJzhu4sGibiqnQ64o6BxhiWQUEk4m9kZb4jCeAuoiV2BzNqF8Qf-c07OFEj5fzSSot83Knw_OguV3qTtPkTRiVzUnnU_\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\" tabindex=\"0\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6JFE9OZfkaU</a></div>', NULL, 1, '2023-07-21 02:12:03', '2023-07-21 02:12:03', NULL),
(578, 'TW-SG Startup Exchange Program', '2023-07-27', '', '<div dir=\"auto\">Ready to expand business oversea in SE Asia?&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">Startup Terrace Kaohsiung is launching Taiwan – Singapore Startup Exchange Program to help you achieve the goal! Eligible candidates will enjoy the perks including bootcamp training, business matching and Singapore expert consultation to learn necessary knowledge for landing.</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">．Registration closes 2023/8/17 23:59pm</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">．More Information: <a href=\"https://reurl.cc/7kmMMy?fbclid=IwAR1C75GCwREnUopp1Sbj0Py72eqTmmdO4UaJhZ63dRnrcVxYfCSH8xB8I4I\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\" tabindex=\"0\" target=\"_blank\">https://reurl.cc/7kmMMy</a></div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">\r\n	<br>\r\n</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">Got questions? Join the Briefing Session to learn more about the program.</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">［Briefing Session］</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">．Time: 2023/8/7/(Mon.) 11:00-11:40am</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">．Registration: <a href=\"https://forms.gle/XVFWQ5MtbX9tDYox7?fbclid=IwAR3EROD-7UlMIxmze3y7TFnncAGWTNcPuliA3hBF5FI1kmCUUbMAJTdZs6M\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\" tabindex=\"0\" target=\"_blank\">https://forms.gle/XVFWQ5MtbX9tDYox7</a></div>', NULL, 1, '2023-07-31 01:25:44', '2023-07-31 01:25:44', NULL),
(579, 'Dotdot unveils one-fit-all payment solution for food businesses', '2023-07-28', '', '<blockquote>\r\n\r\n	<p>Dotdot, a four-year-old fintech startup, launches its innovative product, DDPay. The move marks a significant shift towards digitization for small-scale eateries and more restaurants, a largely untapped market plagued with inefficiencies and labor shortages. The new service built on its main service online ordering platform, will further perfect user experiences with fast and digital processes.</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p>Dotdot has made a splash since its establishment in 2019 under the leadership of CEO Ting Hsieh. Today, with over 15,000 users, 80 million unique users per month, and a staggering total of 50 million orders, Dotdot\'s services have facilitated online financial transactions worth 30 billion. The numbers illustrate an undeniable trend: the era of non-cash payments has arrived, with small-scale eateries increasingly keen to adopt digital solutions. Dotdot positions the product as “payment as a service”, aiming to boost online payments for all businesses.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\"We have witnessed a changing era. In the last three years, the industry has lost nearly 3,000 employees while gaining 20,000 new establishments. Meanwhile, labor costs have skyrocketed, accounting for nearly 40% of expenses,\" said Ting Hsieh, CEO of Dotdot. \"We are committed to easing the burden on these small-scale operations, providing a streamlined solution to save them valuable time, improve service, and reduce labor demands.\"</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"/en/storage/app/media/uploaded-files/1690767341771.jpeg\" alt=\"點點全球執行長謝瑞庭發表了創新支付服務「點點付 DDPay」\" class=\"fr-fic fr-dii\" data-result=\"success\" style=\"width: 900px;\"></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Dotdot positions the product as “payment as a service”, aiming to boost online payments for all businesses. /Photograph : 點點全球</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Hsieh pointed out that the time-consuming tasks of taking phone orders and manual billing take up valuable resources for these establishments, thus taking away from their core service - providing delicious food. He believes non-cash payment is the future, and the Dot Dot Payment solution is designed to simplify this transition, offering a complete, one-stop payment service. It supports QR-based payment methods, and contactless transactions, and eliminates the hassle of dealing with multiple third-party payment providers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\"After payment completion, everything from electronic receipts to loyalty points and carrier services can be handled at one point. We have even integrated services that allow establishments to join the social app LINE members system to help them manage their businesses,\" Hsieh added.\r\n	<br>The new product also promises to resolve one of the major pain points for small businesses – reconciling accounts. The DDPay solution enables businesses to reconcile their accounts via cloud services, offering a streamlined, unified platform for efficient business operations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Bogi Huang, COO of Dotdot, added, \"In the wake of the pandemic, even small-scale and single-person food businesses are gradually accepting digital payment methods. Online payments speed up the process compared to traditional order-taking and cash handling. Our Dot Dot Payment solution is poised to usher these establishments into the future of seamless, digital transactions.\"</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"/en/storage/app/media/uploaded-files/1690767379051.jpeg\" alt=\"點點全球點點付支援信用卡感應支付\" class=\"fr-fic fr-dii\" data-result=\"success\" style=\"width: 900px;\"></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The DDPay solution enables businesses to reconcile their accounts via cloud services, offering a streamlined, unified platform for efficient business operations. /Photograh : 點點全球</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Dotdot Global\'s DDPay service operates through a self-developed interface known as DDUPI, which integrates various online payment channels. The system comprises three core technologies: DDPH for barcodes, DDQR for QR Code scanning, and DDTAP for credit card payments. These are connected through the pre-existing MAP (Member Aggregation Platform) interface, seamlessly integrating features to manage customer membership.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Joel Tay, CEO of Soft Space, which provides contactless credit card payment technology, shared his insights on Dotdot\'s innovative approach. \"Dotdot is the first food tech service platform in Taiwan to provide SoftPOS payment application services,\" he said, \"by utilizing the existing POS machines of businesses and adding contactless credit card payment methods, Dotdot has achieved two major advantages: quick deployment and reduced operational costs. This not only benefits the businesses but also offers consumers a seamless and secure contactless payment experience.\"</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Dotdot\'s use of innovative tech, like Soft Space\'s contactless payment technology, represents a significant step forward in payment solutions. This strategic move towards providing a frictionless experience for both businesses and consumers further solidifies Dotdot\'s commitment to harnessing technology to transform the payment landscape.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Starting as an online ordering platform, Dotdot thrives out of an “accident”</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"/en/storage/app/media/uploaded-files/1690767415969.jpeg\" alt=\"點點全球點點付也支援非餐飲業者的支付\" class=\"fr-fic fr-dii\" data-result=\"success\"></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Dotdot team’s ability to spot a problem and turn it into an opportunity demonstrates the company\'s innovative spirit. /Photograh : 點點全球提供</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The story of Dotdot begins with a simple lunch outing. Bogi Huang and his engineering team found themselves struggling with an overly complicated order machine at a local eatery. This moment sparked the question, \"Is it really that hard? Why don\'t we just build one ourselves?\" This idea birthed the prototype of Dotdot\'s global solution. Initially, it started as a side project – an ordering system that was introduced in May 2019.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, in just six months, the number of businesses using their system soared to 4,500, generating a turnover of more than 300 million. The unexpected success inspired Huang to establish a company and focus on nurturing this promising venture.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Dotdot’s solution capitalizes on technology tools that Taiwanese people use most frequently: LINE. Customers only need to add the restaurant\'s official LINE account to place orders online. The platform offers an array of choices, allowing customers to choose between pick-up, take-out, or delivery. The system seamlessly integrates with popular online payment methods such as Line Pay, making the process extremely convenient for consumers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Dotdot team’s ability to spot a problem and turn it into an opportunity demonstrates the company\'s innovative spirit. The journey from an awkward encounter with a lunch ordering machine to the creation of a robust, user-friendly digital platform embodies Dotdot’s commitment to improving customer experience. This dedication, coupled with their knack for leveraging existing technologies, has been key in Dotdot\'s rapid expansion and success. As the company ventures into the payment solution market, it’s clear that its customer-centric, problem-solving ethos will continue to guide its growth.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>〔Original :Meet Global〕\r\n	<br><a href=\"https://meet-global.bnext.com.tw/articles/view/47938\">https://meet-global.bnext.com.tw/articles/view/47938</a></p>', NULL, 1, '2023-07-31 01:38:44', '2023-09-25 13:35:33', NULL),
(580, 'From Taiwan to Indo-Pacific: The Future of Life Sciences And Health Care', '2023-08-08', '', '<p><strong>The HealthForAll platform is a virtual cross-border collaboration platform</strong>, connecting the international healthcare ecosystem with Taiwan’s dominant industries &amp; startups. The platform provides a unique opportunity for corporate-startup engagement across the areas of medical data, R&amp;D, clinical trials, manufacturing, supply chain, VCs &amp; Investos, and ICT enterprises to foster long-term collaborations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In light of COVD-19 pandemic Taiwan has won global praise for smart healthcare and anti-epidemic ecosystem, furthermore it is our belief that Taiwan is uniquely positioned to drive innovation forward in digital health and the digitalization in healthcare. Thus, we hope to bridge the global healthcare community better understand and engagement the resources &amp; innovation available in Taiwan.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We are extremely proud and grateful that the platform (press conference) has been well received by many partners in Taiwan, including Kaohsiung Medical University &amp; affiliated hospitals, Show Chwan Healthcare System, Sanofi, EPED Inc., AstraZeneca - A. Catalyst Network, JAG, Singapore Biodesign Innovation &amp; Enterprise A*STAR and BE\'s startup alumni.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>The HealthForAll platform is a virtual cross-border collaboration platform:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>HealthForAll helps corporates</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul type=\"disc\">\r\n	<li>achieve inspiration and corporate growth through healthcare startup engagement.</li>\r\n	<li>have an opportunity to provide “reverse pitch” for startups to better understand how they could potentially collaborative and disruptive.</li>\r\n	<li>to engage with startup talents.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>HealthForAll helps startups</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul type=\"disc\">\r\n	<li>bridge the first step in fostering closer corporate-startup relations between Taiwan startups and the international healthcare community.</li>\r\n	<li>leverage the core competencies of Taiwan to accelerate digital transformation in healthcare.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span lang=\"EN-US\">Contact window:&nbsp;</span>\r\n	<br><span lang=\"EN-US\">Graham Sun /<a href=\"mailto:graham.sun@behealthventures.com\" target=\"_blank\">graham.sun@behealthventures.<wbr>com</a>&nbsp;</span>\r\n	<br><span lang=\"EN-US\">Sharon Wei/<a href=\"mailto:sharon.wei@behealthventures.com\" target=\"_blank\">sharon.wei@<wbr>behealthventures.com</a></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span lang=\"EN-US\">&nbsp;<img src=\"/en/storage/app/media/uploaded-files/1691479274047.png\" style=\"width: 900px;\" class=\"fr-fic fr-dib\" data-result=\"success\"></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"/en/storage/app/media/uploaded-files/1691479305351.png\" style=\"width: 900px;\" class=\"fr-fic fr-dib\" data-result=\"success\"></p>', NULL, 1, '2023-08-08 07:24:19', '2023-09-25 13:34:32', NULL);
INSERT INTO `ip_ieit_news` (`id`, `title`, `art_date`, `tag`, `content`, `pic`, `enabled`, `created_at`, `updated_at`, `deleted_at`) VALUES
(581, 'NEXT BIG program from Startup Island TAIWAN unveils 13 innovative startups including AmazingTalker and Hahow', '2023-08-02', '', '<div data-aid=\"47944\">\r\n\r\n	<blockquote>\r\n\r\n		<p>NEXT BIG program, launched by National Development Council and national startup brand Startup Island TAIWAN, has welcome 13 startups this year, getting ready to brew the “next big thing” in the Taiwanese tech ecosystem. These selected startups including well-known education platforms AmazingTalker and Hahow span sectors such as edtech, healthtech, AI cybersecurity, social media, entertainment, fintech, B2B software services, sustainable energy, and aerospace defense technology, a testament to Taiwan’s diversity and strengths in innovation.</p>\r\n\r\n		<p>To enhance Taiwan\'s international recognition in the startup scene, the National Development Council (NDC) has launched the NEXT BIG program under the national startup brand, Startup Island TAIWAN. This initiative aims to promote and showcase promising startups recommended by the startup community and industry leaders as the \"NEXT BIG thing.\"</p>\r\n	</blockquote>\r\n\r\n	<p>By symbolizing their role as frontrunners, the program aims to inspire more young entrepreneurs to embrace innovation. Following the selection of nine NEXT BIG startups in 2021, the NDC has now recommended 13 startups for this year. And the latest wave of 13 startups covers important sectors such as edtech, healthtech, aerospace defense, sustainability, and the digital economy.</p>\r\n\r\n	<p>According to NDC’s Minister Kung Ming-hsin, NEXT BIG not only serves as the national startup brand ambassador but also represents the potential for disruptive innovation across different industries, much like Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Company (TSMC). While Taiwan\'s entrepreneurs have laid a solid foundation for the country\'s global technological partnership through their perseverance and hard work in the past, the future relies on more startup businesses to drive industrial transformation and accelerate Taiwan\'s innovative development on the international stage.</p>\r\n\r\n	<h2>The 13 NEXT BIG are:</h2>\r\n\r\n	<p><a href=\"https://meet-global.bnext.com.tw/articles/view/47603\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>AmazingTalker</strong></a> : Established in 2016, AmazingTalker is an edtech startup offering a platform that connects language learners with tutors from around the world. Their service caters to over 60 languages, making language learning accessible and personalized.</p>\r\n\r\n	<p><a href=\"https://meet-global.bnext.com.tw/articles/view/45910\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Hahow</strong></a> : Founded in 2015, Hahow is an online learning platform that offers a diverse range of creative and practical courses. The startup has raised more than $10 million in total. It is committed to empowering individuals to learn skills in an engaging and interactive way.</p>\r\n\r\n	<p><a href=\"https://us.getcubo.com/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>CuboAi</strong></a> : Founded in 2017, CuboAi is a healthtech startup dedicated to ensuring child safety with AI technology. They provide an AI-powered smart baby monitor which has been recognized for its innovative design and function.</p>\r\n\r\n	<p><strong><a href=\"https://meet-global.bnext.com.tw/articles/view/38554\" target=\"_blank\">Health2Sync</a></strong> : Established in 2013, Health2Sync provides patient-centric diabetes management solutions with its healthtech platform. The Health2Sync app was selected by Healthline as one of the \"10 Best Diabetes Apps\" for 3 consecutive years since 2017 and has over 1,000,000 users worldwide currently.</p>\r\n\r\n	<p><strong><a href=\"https://cycraft.com/\" target=\"_blank\">CyCraft</a></strong> : Founded in 2017, CyCraft is an AI cybersecurity firm dedicated to providing businesses with AI-driven cybersecurity solutions and threat intelligence,serving enterprise customers in FSI, High Tech Manufacturing, and Government agencies. Headquartered in Taiwan with offices in Japan, Singapore, and the USA, the startup is backed by top global VCs including Singapore sovereign fund Temasek’s subsidiary and Pavillion Capital.</p>\r\n\r\n	<p><strong><a href=\"https://meet-global.bnext.com.tw/articles/view/47852\" target=\"_blank\">Gogolook</a></strong> : Established in 2012, Gogolook is known for its mobile application Whoscall. They focus on AI trust technology to provide real-time call screening and personal privacy services. Gogolook announced that it has applied to be listed on the Taiwan Innovation Board (TIB) of the Taiwan Stock Exchange (TWSE) this January. The software’s main service, whoscall, covers markets such as Thailand, Japan, South Korea, Hong Kong, Brazil, and Malaysia, with over 100 million total downloads.</p>\r\n\r\n	<p><strong><a href=\"https://www.dcard.tw/f\" target=\"_blank\">Dcard</a></strong> : Founded in 2011, Dcard is a social media platform popular among students in Taiwan. With its anonymous feature, it\'s a space for open and honest conversations.</p>\r\n\r\n	<p><strong><a href=\"https://meet-global.bnext.com.tw/articles/view/47759\" target=\"_blank\">FunNow</a></strong> : Established in 2015, FunNow provides instant booking services for entertainment and leisure activities, supporting spontaneous urban lifestyles with technology. From Taiwan, the startup has now expanded to Hongkong, Japan, and Malaysia.</p>\r\n\r\n	<p><strong><a href=\"https://inline.app/\" target=\"_blank\">Inline</a></strong> : Established in 2013, Inline is a startup providing reservation services and restaurant management software. They aim to streamline business operations in the hospitality industry.</p>\r\n\r\n	<p>EUI: Founded in 2018, EUI is a fintech startup providing an array of insurance products and solutions. They aim to bridge the gap between customers and insurance products with technology.</p>\r\n\r\n	<p><strong><a href=\"https://www.gofreight.com/\" target=\"_blank\">GoFreight</a></strong> : established in 2017, it revolutionizes the freight forwarding industry as the world\'s largest cloud-based all-in-one software. Our mission is to empower the $300 billion international freight forwarding market by redefining the operating system through cutting-edge technology. We provide comprehensive solutions that simplify, streamline, and optimize freight forwarding operations, delivering unparalleled efficiency and profitability. With GoFreight\'s innovative products, forwarders can reduce costs, increase sales, effortlessly adapt to the digital era, and gain a competitive edge in the global market.</p>\r\n\r\n	<p><strong><a href=\"https://meet-global.bnext.com.tw/articles/view/47616\" target=\"_blank\">NextDrive</a></strong> : Founded in 2013, NextDrive is a sustainable energy startup focused on creating IoT devices to make energy use more efficient and sustainable. After securing a USD$ 31M Series C fund at the end of 2021, NextDrive scales up in Taiwan and also enter the international market.</p>\r\n\r\n	<p><strong><a href=\"https://tronfuture.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Tron Future</a></strong> : Established in 2018, Tron Future is an aerospace defense technology startup specializing in the development of aerospace systems and solutions. They are committed to pushing boundaries in aerospace technology. The company is supported by over 100 professional engineers specializing in developing and producing the world’s most advanced electronic scanning radar and satellite communication systems.</p>\r\n\r\n	<p>These startups exemplify excellence in their fields, demonstrate great market potential, and continue to make remarkable contributions to Taiwan\'s vibrant startup ecosystem. The National Development Council (NDC) continues to encourage collaboration with these startups, recognizing their integral role in fueling Taiwan\'s economic growth and global recognition.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n	<br>〔Original :Meet Global〕\r\n	<br><a href=\"https://meet-global.bnext.com.tw/articles/view/47944\">https://meet-global.bnext.com.tw/articles/view/47944</a></p>', NULL, 1, '2023-08-08 09:05:04', '2023-08-08 09:05:04', NULL),
(582, 'Taiwan Stock Exchange set to further attract foreign capital with newly launched ESG InfoHub and Investment InfoHub', '2023-08-04', '', '<p>Starting from 2022, the company listed on the Taiwan Stock Exchange (the \"<strong>TWSE</strong>\") that has a minimum paid-in capital of NT$2 billion has to input material information or explanations in English into the Market Observation Post System. And then, starting from 2024, all companies listed on the TWSE will have to do the same.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To further enhance services for international investors, the TWSE announced the launch of the new <a href=\"https://esg.twse.com.tw/ESG/front/en/#/main/home\">ESG InfoHub</a> and <a href=\"https://www.twse.com.tw/IIH/en/index\">Investment InfoHub – The Taiwan Markets Dashboard</a> to establish a one-stop information service platform, so as to further strengthen the services for international investors. TWSE hopes to improve the information transparency of listed companies, enhance its competitiveness among international markets, and continue to attract foreign investment to Taiwan.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This year, Taiwan\'s capital market has shown tremendous strength with resilient fundamentals, high dividend returns, and a complete upstream and downstream supply chain in information and communication technology (ICT) industry. The recent AI frenzy, together with the expected end to US rate hikes, has attracted the foreign capital flow to return to Taiwan\'s stock market. So far in 2023, the proportion of foreign capital in Taiwan stocks exceeded 40%, which has driven up stock prices in Taiwan. According to data from TWSE, as of June 30, Taiwan\'s stock market was up 19.65% for the year, ranking fourth among the world\'s major stock markets, and second only to the Japanese stock market 27% among Asian stock markets.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The total revenue of listed companies in Taiwan hit a record high of USD 1.31 trillion in 2022, with an annual growth rate of more than 5%. Judging from the estimated distributable cash for dividends, the estimated dividend yield is close to 5%, ranking among the best in the world. Among the constituent stocks of the Taiwan stock index, listed companies in technology, semiconductors and electronic components have a combined weight of more than 50%.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Optimization of information disclosure with a one-stop service platform</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Investment InfoHub website aims to provide investors with one-stop integrated information services for making investment decisions. It integrates important information from the official website of the TWSE, Market Observation Post System and Market Information System websites. The key information of the markets and listed companies are presented with graphics and visualized analytic reports, providing investors with infographics to facilitate their use in comparison and analysis. In addition, all data reports provide outputs in various file formats such as pictures and tables, allowing investors to further process and utilize the data. By establishing the Investment InfoHub website, TWSE hopes to provide investors, especially foreign institutional investors, with a one-stop access to crucial reference materials needed for making investment decisions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"https://startup.sme.gov.tw/en/storage/app/media/uploaded-files/1691485615739.jpeg\" class=\"fr-fic fr-dii\" data-result=\"success\" style=\"width: 900px;\"></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>The TWSE\'s Investment InfoHub website offers integrated information services for investors to facilitate their investment decision-making.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The ESG InfoHub website integrates ESG information, ESG products and other data from listed companies to make ESG-related information more accessible and useful to investors as an investment reference. Investors may use the platform to look for E (Environment), S (Social), and G (Governance) information of specific companies, and make comparison between companies and across industries to identify the opportunities in the ESG market. The launch of ESG InfoHub, which aims to facilitate ESG investment and drives sustainable finance, represents a critical milestone in the TWSE\'s commitment to promoting the ESG ecosystem, making ESG a competitive advantage for Taiwanese companies in the global market and enhancing the international competitiveness of the capital market as a whole.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"https://startup.sme.gov.tw/en/storage/app/media/uploaded-files/1691485869442.png\" style=\"width: 900px;\" class=\"fr-fic fr-dib\" data-result=\"success\"></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>The TWSE\'s ESG InfoHub website consolidates ESG data and products from listed companies, making them easily accessible and valuable to investors as an investment reference.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Adopting the approach of \"Taiwan going out, the world coming in”, led by Chairman Sherman Lin, TWSE will arrange a delegation visit to New York, the global financial hub, for overseas roadshows and physical meetings with important institutional investors in September, in addition to their visits to Singapore, Malaysia, Japan and Vietnam during the first half of the year. The upcoming visit to New York aims to bolster Taiwan\'s positioning in the international capital market, build long-term relationships and collaboration with major international financial institutions, and attract more foreign investment flow.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Launching new economy industry index to cover four new industry categories</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Along with ESG InfoHub and Investment InfoHub, TWSE has also launched several new key measures in July, including adjustments to the industry classification of listed companies by adding four new categories, namely \"Digital and Cloud Services\" (four companies), \"Sports and Leisure\" (15 companies), \"Green Energy and Environmental Services\" (12 companies), and \"Household\" (11 companies), which allows distinctive listed companies to benefit from a clustering effect and draw the attention of investors. Taking the world\'s largest sports footwear OEM Pou Chen Group and the world\'s leading bicycle manufacturer Giant Group as examples, the two conglomerates, which were originally listed under the \"Other\" category, will be included in the \"Sports and Leisure\" industry category starting from July.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In tandem with the above measures, TWSE will also launch the \"Taiwan New Economy Industry Index\", which covers the listed companies of the four said new industries, as well as the \"Taiwan Innovation Board Index\" to highlight Taiwan\'s new economy companies.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In addition, the TWSE is set to launch a new Corporate Identification System (CIS) in July since the last update 15 years ago in 2008, the new CIS design aims to convey the importance of innovation highly valued by the TWSE.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The TWSE provides introductory videos for <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Azqe9xJR_B8\">ESG InfoHub</a> and <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BZAi_u1XnZo\">Investment InfoHub</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For further information, please contact Mr. Tsai at <a href=\"mailto:1193@twse.com.tw\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">1193@twse.com.tw</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>〔The original article: <a href=\"https://twmonthly.twse.com.tw/front/content/8a8185be8915fd3301894d5b75880005?date=\" target=\"_blank\">Taiwan Stock Exchange set to further attract foreign capital with newly launched ESG InfoHub and Investment InfoHub</a>〕</p>', NULL, 1, '2023-08-08 09:16:11', '2023-09-25 13:33:13', NULL),
(583, 'Here comes the winners for 2023 G Camp', '2023-08-16', '', '<div dir=\"auto\">Congrats to the winning team!!\r\n	<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\"><strong>【KPMG Global Tech Innovator &amp; G Camp Go Global Accelerating Award】</strong></div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">．Lypid</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">\r\n	<br><strong>【G Camp Go Global Accelerating Award】</strong></div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">．AIPLUX Technology&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">．EMILY.RPA&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">．FaceHeart&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">．Numbers Protocol&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">．Slasify&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">．Turing Space&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">．VM-Fi&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">\r\n	<br><strong>【StartupGoGo Go Japan Award】</strong></div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">．Avalanche Computing Taiwan\r\n	<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\"><strong>【STARTUP101 Golden Awards】</strong></div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">．Charco Science and Research&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">．ness wellness</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">．NeuinX</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">． PET100PERCENT</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">．Ranictek</div>', NULL, 1, '2023-08-16 08:01:23', '2023-08-16 08:01:23', NULL),
(584, 'MEGABAY is going to depart from 85 Sky Tower, Kaohsiung, leading the startup partners to the globe!', '2023-08-17', '', '<p>Special guests, \'Fukuoka Smart EAST\' and \'Malaysia Digital Economy Corporation (MDEC)\', are invited to this international event, mutually exploring the application of innovative technology in smart city and digital economy, bringing more energy into the three-party innovation ecosystem.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Kaohsiung, with the strengths of harbor and airport, the feature industry, and innovation field, is the best stage for enterprises to deploy the globe and international. MEGABAY will comprehansively connect with cooperation opportunities by assisting start-up and enterprises, winning orders in the international market.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>◆ &nbsp;Time: 2023.08.31 (Thu.) 13:00-16:00</strong>\r\n	<br><strong>◆</strong>&nbsp; <strong>Place: 19F, No. 3, Ziqiang 3rd Rd., Lingya Dist., Kaohsiung City (85 Sky Tower)<br></strong><strong>◆</strong>&nbsp; <strong>Participants: Start-ups, groups, companies, who are interested in international market.<br></strong><strong>◆</strong>&nbsp; <strong>Fee: Free</strong>\r\n	<br>*Event in ENGLISH</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Contact for further information\r\n	<br>MEGABAY Ms. Hsieh | +886-7-566-6686 | +886-910-512688\r\n	<br>E-mail：emily.megabay@gmail.com</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Organizer | Economic Development Bureau, Kaohsiung City Government\r\n	<br>Implementer | Taipei Computer Association</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, 1, '2023-08-16 08:21:35', '2023-09-25 02:11:44', NULL),
(585, 'Together, Go Big. SWITCH 2023', '2023-08-18', '', '<div dir=\"auto\">With the backing of NDC and MOEA, Startup Island TAIWAN is set to showcase the pinnacle of Taiwan\'s startup ecosystem at the Singapore Week of Innovation and Technology (SWITCH), taking place from 31 Oct to 2 Nov.</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">\r\n	<br>\r\n</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">Embark on an exciting journey across SEAsia starting from SWITCH Singapore! Discover the vibrant Startup Island TAIWAN Pavilion, engage in dynamic global expert forums, foster connections with industry titans through networking, and delve into enlightening corporate visits. Your gateway to a transformative experience awaits!\r\n	<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">Domain Applications:</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">． Digital Transformation and Smart City (Fintech included)</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">． Health and BioTech</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">． Environment and Green Tech</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">． Smart Manufacturing and Supply Chain\r\n	<br>\r\n	<br>\r\n</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">Join us: <a href=\"https://forms.gle/8JnZbfiCrzTDCWHD9?fbclid=IwAR3j96BnULIg5iOpyOKPYI-udguRGOLqGstMMN1FfyhRGFK_0JuiCxa8EOI\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\" tabindex=\"0\" target=\"_blank\">https://forms.gle/8JnZbfiCrzTDCWHD9</a>\r\n	<br>Contact: <a href=\"mailto:charles@startupislandtaiwan.info\">charles@startupislandtaiwan.info</a>,<a href=\"mailto:serena@startupislandtaiwan.info\">&nbsp;serena@startupislandtaiwan.info</a></div>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n	<br>\r\n</p>', NULL, 1, '2023-08-23 09:17:32', '2023-08-23 09:17:59', NULL),
(586, 'Join us at the upcoming exhibition -Meet Greater South!', '2023-08-23', '', '<p>As one of the leading startup expos in Asia, Meet Greater South is the largest go-to platform for startups and all the key players in the local and global ecosystem, including venture capitalists, investors, corporates, incubators, accelerators, service-providers, media and government initiatives.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This August, Meet Greater South presents non-stop conferences, demo days, talks, biz meetings and networking events, providing 260+ startups and key partners to meet and connect in 2 days.</p>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">\r\n	<br>\r\n</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">．Exhibition Date: August 25-26</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">．Venue: Kaohsiung Exhibition Center( No.39, Chenggong 2nd Rd., Qianzhen Dist., Kaohsiung, Taiwan)</div>\r\n\r\n<p>．More info: <a href=\"https://eng.meetgreatersouth.tw/\">https://eng.meetgreatersouth.tw/</a></p>', NULL, 1, '2023-08-23 09:25:58', '2023-08-23 09:26:12', NULL),
(587, 'TTA 5th Anniversary Celebration', '2023-09-01', '', '<p>TTA (Taiwan Tech Arena), the most crucial innovation and entrepreneurship ecosystem in Taiwan, is celebrating its fifth anniversary this year. Several events are planned to retrospect TTA\'s development over the past five years and look forward to the future: In addition to strengthening support for Taiwan\'s tech startups, TTA is actively attracting international IC startups to Taiwan. Through various international forums, the aim is to explore how international collaborations can enhance startup scale-up and global expansion, while driving continuous innovation and industry advancement. Alongside these initiatives, XYZ panel discussions will be held to foster novel opportunities at the intersection of technology and culture.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Date and Time: </strong>September 11, 2023 (Monday) 09:30-15:20\r\n	<br><strong>Venue: </strong>Level 3 Grand Ballroom, Grand Hyatt Taipei (No. 2, Songshou Road, Xinyi District, Taipei City)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>More info &amp; Registration</strong>\r\n	<br><a href=\"https://isti.surveycake.biz/s/9Rrqq\">https://isti.surveycake.biz/s/9Rrqq</a></p>', NULL, 1, '2023-09-01 07:12:09', '2023-09-01 07:12:09', NULL),
(588, '2023 Meet Greater South Expo anchors Taiwan to the world', '2023-09-01', '', '<p>Startup Terrace Kaohsiung just wrapped up an inspiring 2023 Meet Greater South Expo. There are 17 startup teams showcased innovations and forged connections over two dynamic days. From compelling pitches to networking, every moment brimmed with passion. The Expo’s atmosphere was electric, leaving us in awe of the innovations. Grateful for this platform to connect, learn, and grow together. As the Expo concludes, our determination remains unwavering. We\'ll persist, innovate, and pursue our vision. Thanks for the support; our journey is just beginning. </p>', NULL, 1, '2023-09-01 07:41:54', '2023-09-01 07:41:54', NULL),
(589, 'Entrepreneur Visa Online Applications Now Available!', '2023-09-02', '', '<div dir=\"auto\">To facilitate foreign nationals in starting businesses in Taiwan, starting from July 1, 2023, the Entrepreneur Visa application process has been optimized as follows:</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">1. Applications are now entirely online.</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">2. Initial visa duration extended to 2 years.</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">\r\n	<br>\r\n</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">Providing foreign entrepreneurs with a more convenient process and ample preparation time for business establishment!</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">How\r\n	<a tabindex=\"-1\"></a>to apply?</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">Please register an account and submit your application on “Foreign Professionals Online Application Platform” -&gt; <a href=\"https://reurl.cc/M8KMMn?fbclid=IwAR3rmWI7ykvE6TGEhlE5mDnU0TR8tTnqfGxim0x0An1I-LjyZzHWQ1qxraE\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\" tabindex=\"0\" target=\"_blank\">https://reurl.cc/M8KMMn</a></div>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"/en/storage/app/media/uploaded-files/EV2.jpg\" style=\"width: 600px;\" class=\"fr-fic fr-dib\" data-result=\"success\"></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"/en/storage/app/media/uploaded-files/EV1.jpg\" style=\"width: 600px;\" class=\"fr-fic fr-dib\" data-result=\"success\"></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"/en/storage/app/media/uploaded-files/EV3.jpg\" style=\"width: 600px;\" class=\"fr-fic fr-dib\" data-result=\"success\"></p>', NULL, 1, '2023-09-01 09:28:44', '2023-10-03 01:59:36', NULL),
(590, 'AR for Her - Meta Spark Workshop', '2023-09-13', '', '<div dir=\"auto\">AWE Taiwan is grateful to be invited to join【AR for Her Workshop】at the American Innovation Center on September 7th and 8th. This training camp is supported by Meta Taiwan and AIT , featured prominent speakers and revolved around the trending topic of the metaverse. The workshop covered theoretical applications, case studies, and hands-on experiences, gradually immersing participants in the world of AR and guiding them through the step-by-step design and implementation of various AR effects.</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">\r\n	<br>\r\n</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">Assistant Cultural Affairs Officer Julienne Lauler from AIT and Max Chen, Head of Public Policy at Meta, were present to deliver remarks. Over 2 day of the workshops, trainees were able to come up with marketing strategies incorporated with AR. &nbsp;This is the main purpose of the workshop that allows entrepreneurs learn how to utilize technology. &nbsp;</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">\r\n	<br>\r\n</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">For more information about AWE Taiwan, please visit <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/AWEinTaiwan?__cft__[0]=AZW27-_VUnNHNMZzt5C7f1nSjC9z4V_ZNWkxzFuhnAfRdstdUKYQNtUPs9BkHXTQOoLAqdHAxuDqI1iZMti1LY950dNeEc4FxcKlFfMaSekkYFBIHb2zffSjV570QhUEa1Dyteb5N7xWHMR2elFqxtGpSOHI2QaGdx4x6-YOHEsinlykUrE-vfybqNSDP71gsHQ&amp;__tn__=-]K-R\" tabindex=\"0\">https://www.facebook.com/AWEinTaiwan</a> for more updates.</div>', NULL, 1, '2023-09-13 09:08:53', '2023-09-13 09:08:53', NULL),
(591, 'Pledging over US$300 million to creativity and originality, Taiwan’s largest crowdfunding platform Zeczec marks its milestone', '2023-09-08', '', '<blockquote>\r\n\r\n	<p>Since the first-ever crowdfunding platform Zeczec was founded in 2012, more than 7,000 projects have generated over ten billion Taiwanese dollars, which is equivalent to 300 million U.S. dollars. Emphasizing creativity and originality, the crowdfunding platform had over 60% of pledged money going to projects featuring original creations such as the world’s first palm-sized laser engraver provider Cubiio.</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p>As Taiwan’s first crowdfunding platform, Zeczec marked its milestone by pledging over $300 million altogether for 7,000 projects. Quake Hsu, the co-founder of Zeczec, emphasized the platform\'s unwavering commitment to three key pillars: fostering genuine originality, celebrating the richness of Taiwanese cultures, and catalyzing local industries.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>“We not only contribute to these three core values in the last decade, but also we would like to level up and speed up market validation for original creativity,” said Hsu. Taking this commitment a step further, Zeczec is launching a subsidiary to directly invest in innovative and original ideas. This strategic move not only underscores the platform’s dedication to nurturing early-stage creativity but also equips budding ideas with the necessary resources and support, aiding them in their growth journey.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Zeczec: A Global Contender in the Crowdfunding Arena</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"https://startup.sme.gov.tw/en/storage/app/media/uploaded-files/1694597041949.jpeg\" alt=\"Global Crowdfunding Platforms \" class=\"fr-fic fr-dii\" data-result=\"success\" style=\"width: 900px;\"></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Zeczec has pledged over US$300 million within a decade and boasts a success rate of over 78% for its crowdfunding projects, ranking No.1 in project success rate. / Image Credits: Wendy Wu</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In the dynamic world of crowdfunding, Zeczec has emerged as a formidable force, not just within Taiwan but on the global stage as well. While platforms like Indiegogo, Kickstarter, and Japan\'s Campfire have long been recognized names in the crowdfunding universe, Zeczec\'s commitment to fostering creativity and originality sets it apart.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The platform has pledged over US$300 million within a decade and boasts a success rate of over 78% for its crowdfunding projects. This high success rate is a testament to its dedication to innovation and its deep-seated belief in the potential of original ideas. While the global crowdfunding giant Kickstarter has seen more than 70 billion dollars pledged and a 39.4% success rate, Japan’s crowdfunding platform, Campfire, has a total pledged amount of over 500 million and a success rate of 26% for projects reaching their funding goals. Indiegogo, which doesn’t disclose its total funded amount, has a success rate of only 9%. The combination of its user-centric approach, robust infrastructure, and keen market insights makes Zeczec a promising contender in the future of crowdfunding.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As Zeczec gears up to challenge the giants in the crowdfunding realm, the company has set ambitious targets for itself. Determined to grow both rapidly and strategically, Zeczec has embarked on an audacious journey to amass its next US$300 million within a span of just three years, targeting 2026. To speed up its crowdfunding pace, Zeczec adopts a strategy of selecting and marketing projects with strong cultural roots.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Setting off a craze of eco-friendly beverage cups and classic literature, Zeczec becomes a cultural hub</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"https://startup.sme.gov.tw/en/storage/app/media/uploaded-files/1694597067477.jpeg\" alt=\"嘖嘖創辦人徐震\" class=\"fr-fic fr-dii\" data-result=\"success\" style=\"width: 900px;\"></p>\r\n\r\n<p>In an era where ideas transcend borders and innovation knows no bounds, Zeczec stands poised to be a beacon for creators and innovators worldwide. / Image Credits: 嘖嘖</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Throughout its journey, Zeczec has been instrumental in propelling numerous products from different industries into the spotlight. The platform\'s impressive success stories speak to its efficacy and impact. Notably, Hiding Tou, marked one of the most supported projects on the platform, has produced the “national beverage cup”. With an initial goal of NT$ 1,000,000, the campaign amassed an astonishing NT$ 38,289,487 from 31,089 supporters, indicating the vast potential and appeal of native Taiwanese products.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Furthermore, Yuan-Liou Publishing, the renowned publishing house, has successfully utilized Zeczec to rejuvenate and reintroduce a series of novels by the legendary Chinese writer Jin Yong, whose works have garnered sales of over 300 million copies globally. In a similar vein, the celebrated “Agatha Christie: The Queen of Crime”, has also been freshly relaunched on the platform.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Traditional Taiwanese industries are witnessing an evolution of business models, with individuals leveraging the platform to foster collaborations, as seen in a collaboration melding 80 years of traditional Japanese craftsmanship with Taiwanese design. This fusion culminated in products that blend Taiwan\'s innovative designs with Japan\'s impeccable manufacturing standards.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Moreover, Zeczec extends its reach beyond Taiwan\'s shores, inviting international talents and brilliant ideas to the island. The platform successfully funded over 1,400 cultural content projects. An English illustrator Tom Parker, through the platform\'s support, was able to complete his illustrative masterpiece, the “Taipei Map.”</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n	<iframe width=\"560\" height=\"315\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/ZwUCNEN90qA?enablejsapi=1&amp;origin=https%3A%2F%2Fmeet-global.bnext.com.tw\" title=\"《台北地圖》藝術家專訪 | Taipei map illustrator interview 中文字幕\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\" data-gtm-yt-inspected-36661081_219=\"true\" data-gtm-yt-inspected-43=\"true\" data-gtm-yt-inspected-48=\"true\" data-gtm-yt-inspected-81=\"true\"></iframe>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In an era where ideas transcend borders and innovation knows no bounds, Zeczec stands poised to be a beacon for creators and innovators worldwide. Its trajectory suggests not just growth in numbers, but an evolution in how ideas are funded, nurtured, and brought to life on the global stage.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>〔Original :Meet Global〕\r\n	<br><a href=\"https://meet-global.bnext.com.tw/articles/view/47960\">https://meet-global.bnext.com.tw/articles/view/47960</a></p>', NULL, 1, '2023-09-13 09:27:46', '2023-09-25 13:30:35', NULL),
(592, 'Announcing the 2023 UAE Market Access & Expand North Star Startup Show Tour!', '2023-09-19', '', '<div dir=\"auto\">We are currently recruiting startups interested in expanding to the <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/hashtag/middleeast?__eep__=6&amp;__cft__[0]=AZVOdM4WJBEfPG0wYHt9cZ16lGmp88DgI_ECYeC1NIfY_DieiSNWosTmpt9mXeqKmq2xnDbSVvUXITfFsdn8Qf2-Uuk43Q2GmFGK2wS47J82EAvLJzUMoMGBwWMCiWmdw_4AELhz-FE_x-ltVrjDk2bdJwBCFAp1az3tJ1NJlc9gb9pvvp7GVtp5Amhfigf3xQoHm4m5ReStwmUoqbtjafzx&amp;__tn__=*NK-y-R\" tabindex=\"0\">#MiddleEast</a> and specifically the <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/hashtag/uae?__eep__=6&amp;__cft__[0]=AZVOdM4WJBEfPG0wYHt9cZ16lGmp88DgI_ECYeC1NIfY_DieiSNWosTmpt9mXeqKmq2xnDbSVvUXITfFsdn8Qf2-Uuk43Q2GmFGK2wS47J82EAvLJzUMoMGBwWMCiWmdw_4AELhz-FE_x-ltVrjDk2bdJwBCFAp1az3tJ1NJlc9gb9pvvp7GVtp5Amhfigf3xQoHm4m5ReStwmUoqbtjafzx&amp;__tn__=*NK-y-R\" tabindex=\"0\">#UAE</a>. Judging will be in English and be hold online next Tuesday/Wednesday. All the preparation of Taiwan delegation will be completed in next 3 weeks. Government subsidies will be provided for selected 5 startup companies.</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">\r\n	<br>\r\n</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">Target Fields:</div>\r\n<div dir=\"auto\">We\'re looking for Taiwanese startups with a strong interest in the following fields: <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/hashtag/aiot?__eep__=6&amp;__cft__[0]=AZVOdM4WJBEfPG0wYHt9cZ16lGmp88DgI_ECYeC1NIfY_DieiSNWosTmpt9mXeqKmq2xnDbSVvUXITfFsdn8Qf2-Uuk43Q2GmFGK2wS47J82EAvLJzUMoMGBwWMCiWmdw_4AELhz-FE_x-ltVrjDk2bdJwBCFAp1az3tJ1NJlc9gb9pvvp7GVtp5Amhfigf3xQoHm4m5ReStwmUoqbtjafzx&amp;__tn__=*NK-y-R\" tabindex=\"0\">#AIoT</a> <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/hashtag/robotic?__eep__=6&amp;__cft__[0]=AZVOdM4WJBEfPG0wYHt9cZ16lGmp88DgI_ECYeC1NIfY_DieiSNWosTmpt9mXeqKmq2xnDbSVvUXITfFsdn8Qf2-Uuk43Q2GmFGK2wS47J82EAvLJzUMoMGBwWMCiWmdw_4AELhz-FE_x-ltVrjDk2bdJwBCFAp1az3tJ1NJlc9gb9pvvp7GVtp5Amhfigf3xQoHm4m5ReStwmUoqbtjafzx&amp;__tn__=*NK-y-R\" tabindex=\"0\">#Robotic</a> <a href=\"htt